title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Fit bottom crust into 9-inch pie plate.
Break Ritz coarsely into crust.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in small saucepan.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind. Cool.
Pour over crackers, dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Trim and flute edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 425°
for 30 to 35 minutes, or until crust is crisp and golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 slices.

title: pepper relish
directions: Place peppers and onions in saucepan.
Cover with water. Bring to boil.
Remove from fire and let stand 10 minutes; drain. Mix sugar, vinegar and spices; bring to a boil in separate saucepan.
Add peppers and onions to sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Cook slowly 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars; seal.
Process in water bath.
Cool and store.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves (about 5 minutes).
Mix onion, rice and egg; add to ground beef.
Salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture into cabbage leaf.
Arrange in Dutch oven.

title: american meat loaf
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onion and saute together with celery and garlic until tender, about 5 to 6 minutes. Combine ground beef, pork and bread crumbs in a large bowl. Add sauteed vegetables, salt, pepper to taste, nutmeg, cayenne, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and water. Mix thoroughly by hands. Pat meat loaf in oval shaped mound in 11 x 7-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: late-night breadsticks
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the fist five ingredients; set aside.
Divide dough into 16 pieces; roll each into a 6 inch rope. Dip ropes in butter, then roll in cheese mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Let rise for 10 minutes.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 16 breadsticks.

title: icebox cake
directions: Crumble cake in baking dish or pan.
Pour cooked pudding over cake; chill.
Prepare Dream Whip; put on top of pudding and cake mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Clean and hull strawberries.
Put into bowl with 1 cup sugar. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: preacher cookies 1
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt, margarine and milk. Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oatmeal and raisins if desired.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Set aside. Mix coconut and pecans and spread on bottom of greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cake batter on coconut and pecans.
Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook frozen spinach according to directions on package. Combine cooled, drained spinach with sour cream, mayonnaise, dry onion soup mix, lemon juice, seasoned salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Chill and serve with corn chips.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Simmer all ingredients.
Remove from heat and allow to cool for an hour before straining.
Add to 2 gallons apple cider and heat together gently.
Garnish with orange slices stuck with whole cloves and serve hot.
Use whole cinnamon sticks for stirring.

title: mock condensed milk
directions: Put warm water in bowl.
Add milk powder and mix well.
Add sugar and mix well.
Set bowl in a pan of hot water while mixing, if the sugar does not dissolve completely.

title: reunite hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in a skillet.
Drain well.
Add Manwich, green pepper, salt, wine, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: coconut brown sugar cake
directions: Combine cereal and boiling water and set aside 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sift flour with baking soda and baking powder.
Combine shortening, sugar and vanilla; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs; beat 1 minute longer.
Add dry ingredients and cereal.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread topping on cake. Broil until brown.

title: cucumber rounds
directions: Mix cream cheese with Good Seasons Italian.
Spread on party bread.
Place one thinly sliced piece of cucumber on; sprinkle with dill.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil squash for 5 to 10 minutes.
Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Season with salt and pepper and Italian seasoning.
Add garlic, tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, then top with Mozzarella cheese until melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Combine 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar in bag.
Add biscuits and shake to coat.
Mix margarine, brown sugar, condensed milk, remaining 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done. Save broth. Cool chicken and tear apart into pieces. Fry bell pepper and onion together until tender. Boil spaghetti in broth with bouillon cubes. Mix together Ro-Tel and soups. Place chicken, spaghetti (well drained), bell pepper and onion into 10 x 13 pan or larger. Pour soup mix over and mix. Cut cheese into cubes and place on top of spaghetti mix. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chicken, soup and chilies.
In 9 x 13 inch pan, pour some enchilada sauce to cover the bottom of pan. Tear tortillas in half and place one layer on bottom of pan.
Pour some sauce over tortillas.
Then add a layer of the chicken mixture, 1/3 of the shredded cheese and dollop 1/3 of the sour cream around layer.
Cover with a layer of tortillas and 1/4 of enchilada sauce.
Repeat with another layer of chicken mixture, cheese and sour cream, tortillas and enchilada sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce, spread cheese and dollops of sour cream.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry-lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease or place paper liner in twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
In medium bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and stir in grated lemon peel.
In large bowl, beat egg with milk and oil; add flour mixture, stirring just to combine ingredients.
Be careful not to beat batter too much.
It should have a few lumps.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons sugar; fold the blueberries into batter.
Spoon the batter into paper liners, filling them 2/3 full.
Bake the muffins in the 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
While muffins are still warm, dump the tops in melted butter and remaining sugar.

title: cracker spread
directions: Place the cream cheese on a plate.
Cover with the cocktail sauce.
Top with shrimp.
Serve with crackers.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With fork, mix together flour, salt, shortening and vinegar. In separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until blended.
Chill for at least 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 single crusts.

title: green tomato soy(good)
directions: Slice tomatoes;
put
in layers with onion and peppers. Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Add spices.
Cover with vinegar and cook until tender.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: vegetarian chili(heart healthy)
directions: To rehydrate TVP, mix equal portions of TVP with hot water. Let sit 5 minutes.
Saute onion, jalapeno and garlic in wine.
Add tomato.
Cook until desired texture has been reached.
Add black beans, cumin, bay and chili powder.
Add TVP.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Let chili simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, dry mustard and cornstarch.
Slowly add vinegar, lemon juice, lemon rind, water and raisins.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Delicious on ham.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Hush corn right before cooking.
Sprinkle with butter, salt and pepper.
Wrap each ear tightly in aluminum foil.
Roast on grill 10 to 20 minutes, turning frequently.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Pour in Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: coconut buttermilk pies
directions: Mix well, then pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine margarine, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Mix until chips are melted and smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually blend in the flour mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cream pea soup
directions: In a heavy kettle, bring water to a boil.
Add onion, celery, cauliflower, salt and bouillon.
Return to boil; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add peas, dill, parsley, basil and sage; return to boil.
Cover and simmer additional 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; puree in blender until creamy.
Return to heat.
Add butter; stir while reheating.
This is good with whole wheat toast.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: In a small glass bowl, melt butter.
Add cheese and olive oil. Mix.
Add cream and mix well.
Microwave on High 30 seconds. Stir; microwave 30 seconds.
Stir; microwave 45 seconds or until almost boiling.
Pour over hot fettuccine.
Toss lightly. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Great served with grilled chicken and salad!

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Using a hot 14-inch Dutch oven, coat bottom of pan with the oil.
Thinly
slice
garlic and onions and saute until you can really smell the aroma.
Thinly slice the potatoes and all into a pan.
Mix
remaining
items
together.
Slice or chunk bell peppers
and
add
to
pan.
Slowly
add
the
milk until covered. Slowly
cook
until
tender.
Add flour and water or cornstarch and
water
to thicken to desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper for taste.

title: pepper nuts (pfeffernuesse)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add sorghum and eggs.
Mix in remainder of ingredients, using all the flour you can knead in. Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Cover whole cukes with boiling water and allow to stand until the next morning.
Drain and repeat the procedure for the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and cut cukes into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: grandma william's butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together in saucepan brown sugar, butter and water and boil until thick.
Blend in a separate bowl milk, flour and egg yolks.
Mix flour mixture into syrup mixture and cook until thick. Add vanilla and pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: chicken cutlets with tomato
directions: Coat cutlets with nonstick cooking spray and place in heated frying pan.
Saute on both sides for 2 minutes.
Remove and keep warm.
Add oil to pan and saute garlic and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes and wine.
Cook for 10 minutes more.
Place cutlets in pan and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.
Serve with white rice.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Stir butter and sugar together in saucepan over low heat until butter is melted.
Blend in cracker crumbs.
Press evenly into pie pan; chill.
Yield: enough for 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: 6 layer nacho dip
directions: First Layer:
On a regular pizza pan, smooth out an entire can of refried beans.

title: glorified hash
directions: Crumble hash in casserole or 9 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°, or until custard is set.
Partially cool.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Layer a baking dish with crushed pineapple, with juice, then put blueberries over pineapple.
Sprinkle sugar over blueberries. Place dry cake mix on top of sugar and pour melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter and last add chopped pecans,
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.
May use other fruits instead of blueberries.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie pan with Pam spray.
Place all ingredients in blender and blend 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in flour and water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Fold in cheese, broccoli and eggs.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Dot 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: louisiana chicken gumbo
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Make a roux by browning flour with shortening, stirring constantly.
Add chopped onions and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer, or you can add onions later after you have added water.
Add cold water a little at a time, making thick paste. Keep adding water to thin, using skillet to brown flour.
Now change to larger pot and pour thick mixture into pan.
Drop in chicken with salt and pepper.
Add sufficient water to boil 1 hour or until meat is tender, having 3-quarts of liquid when cooked. Add onion tops, parsley, bell pepper and celery.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Turn off fire; add gumbo file.
Stir well.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, and 2/3 cup crushed crackers, salt and pepper to taste. Stir in corn, onion and pimentos. Toss butter with remaining crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake uncovered for one hour at 350°.

title: hobo surprise
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish (or cake pan) as follows: ground beef, onion and potatoes (sliced 1/8-inch thick). Top with honey.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: Blend whole peeled tomatoes.
Combine onion mix, water, lentils, rice, tomatoes, chopped carrot, chopped celery, basil, oregano and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: impossible no-crust pumpkin pie
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Heat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients until thoroughly mixed. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook onions and bell pepper until done. Add Cheddar cheese soup and milk.
Mix well.
Bring to boil.
Pour over noodles and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook until thick as cream (doesn't take long).
Cool.
Pour over chopped cabbage.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add other ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in pecans, dates and cherries.
Chill dough for 1 hour or overnight.

title: stuffed baby spuds
directions: Prick potatoes with fork.
Place in microwave-safe pan and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until fork-tender.
Cool enough to handle.
Hollow out each potato with spoon leaving a sturdy shell.
Puree cottage cheese in food processor until smooth.
Put in small bowl and stir in horseradish, chives, dill and black pepper.
Spoon into potato shells.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat in all ingredients until batter is smooth.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
This makes about 8 1/2 cups.

title: peach bread
directions: Mix everything all together.
Add fruit.
Grease and flour tins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield: Makes 2 regular loaves.

title: sherried wild rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion. Cook and stir about 5 minutes until golden. Add mushrooms and celery. Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Mix in flour.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly, 5 to 8 minutes until slightly thickened.
Stir in rice, salt, curry, mustard, chervil (parsley) and pepper.
Bring to a simmer, stirring occasionally.
Ladle hot soup into individual bowls.
Garnish with parsley or chives. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: stromboli express
directions: Roll bread dough into a 6 x 10-inch rectangle and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Line bread with mustard, meat, vegetables and cheese.
Roll and bake for an additional 15 minutes at 375°.
After taking out of oven, sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Slice and serve.

title: broccoli potato bake
directions: Cook, drain and mash the potatoes with diet margarine, salt and milk.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain well and fold into mashed potatoes.
Put in casserole sprayed with vegetable pan spray.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peach pie(no bake)
directions: Cook peach juice in pan and thicken with sugar and cornstarch. Add peaches.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in graham cracker crust.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash browns with other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange sauce for cake
directions: Beat egg
yolks and mix sugar well.
Add rind and juice of oranges.
Cook
in double boiler until thick.
Let cool and add whipped cream.

title: soy-glazed chicken(low calorie - 275 calories)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain pineapple and reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce, onion, ginger and garlic powder together in a roasting pan.
Add chicken and coat well. Arrange chicken in roaster with skin side up.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, basting with juices occasionally.
Add pineapple and bake an additional 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: main-dish salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except Tangy Red Dressing in a large bowl, reserving some of the mushrooms, tomatoes, ham, cheese and eggs for garnish; toss gently. Arrange reserved ingredients on top of salad. Serve with Tangy Red Dressing. Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: donellan road special sandwich
directions: This is a remarkably tasty and piquant concoction.
The quality of the ingredients is critical.
The red pepper should not be the pickled kind in the jar; the kind from a well stocked deli case is best.
The deli in Scarsdale's C-Town market sells excellent peppers and Feta, too.
Top
the cheese and peppers with capers and eat open-faced or in traditional sandwich form.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dry cake mix.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour blueberry pie filling, then crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry mixture over fruit.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Fold in bread gently.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Good served with ham or pork in place of potatoes.

title: fruit punch
directions: In a punch bowl or large pitcher, combine all ingredients. Serve immediately.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream together, then add remaining ingredients.
Serve with apple wedges, pears, strawberries, grapes and melon.

title: martip toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line pan with parchment paper and lay crackers on, filling tray.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.	Do not brown.
Dust chicken with flour and fry in oil until brown.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add onions, tomatoes, wine, bay leaves and parsley.
Cover tightly and simmer until chicken is fork tender. About 1 hr.
If necessary, baste occasionally with a little wine or chicken broth to prevent sticking.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with a mixture of the flour, salt and a dash of pepper.
Brown in shortening.
Add next 3 ingredients. Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Top with Sour Cream Gravy.

title: sweet squash
directions: Cut squash in half; remove seeds and place face down in shallow pan.
Add 1/2-inch water to pan and bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes, then turn cut side up.
Mix all ingredients in small bowl and pour over squash evenly.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13-inch round pizza pan.
Combine brownie mix, egg, oil and water in a large bowl.
Stir with a spoon until well-blended, about 50 strokes.
Spread into pan. Bake 23 to 27 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Decorate with assorted fruit and cut into wedges.
Top with ice cream and drizzle syrup over top.
tags: brownies plus milk chocolate chunks mix

title: golden honey rolls
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until warm (120°).
In large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, salt, eggs and warm liquid.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining 1 3/4 cups flour.
Cover and let rise until double in size, about 1 hour. Grease large cake pan.
Stir down dough, beating 30 seconds.
Drop by tablespoon of dough side by side.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water together in casserole.
Add rice with seasonings and Chinese vegetables.
Arrange pork chops on top. Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: light spinach dip with water chestnuts
directions: Process cottage cheese in food processor or blender until smooth.
Place in medium bowl and set aside.
Press spinach between paper towels until barly moist.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients to cheese mixture; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate about 3 hours.
Serve with nonfat crackers or fresh raw vegetables.

title: moravian cake
directions: Mix the sugar, 1 cup flour, butter or shortening and salt together like pie dough.
Beat the egg in a cup; fill cup with milk.
Add this to the first mixture, then add 1 cup flour and the baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top add cinnamon and brown sugar.
Dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour.
Add whipping cream and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 325° and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Do not open the door while baking.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Grate potatoes fine, and drain well.
Add salt, crumbs, flour and parsley to make a stiff dough.
Drop into boiling salted water from wet spoon.
Dumplings should be about 1 1/2-inches long and 1/2-inch in diameter when cooked.
They are done as soon as they float to the top.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup BBQ sauce.

title: ralph's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Use for basting chicken, chops or ribs.
Store in a covered jar in refrigerator.

title: harvey wallbanger's cake
directions: Beat
until smooth and spread over cake.
Sprinkle with chopped (fine) nuts.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut and remove after cooking 5 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Soften yeast in water 15 minutes.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and milk.
Add flour, a little at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Knead until smooth.
(Do not add too much flour.)
Cover with a damp, warm cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in 2-inch rounds.
Butter, fold over and butter again.
Place in rows on well-oiled baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until triple in bulk. Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 24 to 30 rolls.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix milk and sugar; boil for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
While cake is hot, prick cake with a fork. Mix coconut with milk and sugar mixture.
Then dribble over cake. Let cool (better overnight).
Mix Cool Whip and 7 ounces coconut with vanilla.
Spread over cool cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer; debone, reserving liquid.
Cook pepper, onion and garlic in small amount of butter (1 to 2 tablespoons) and 1/4 cup liquid until soft and clear.
Add all cans of soup; mix well. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add soup mixture and deboned chicken.
Place in casserole.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
This freezes well.
Serves approximately 8 to 10.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in mold.
Let chill one hour. Spread sour cream over gelatin mixture and spoon remaining mixture on top; chill.
This could be made with dietetic gelatin and dietetic canned pineapple.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°f. 200°c. gas mark 6. Line 12 medium muffin cups or grease the bottoms. Combine the dry ingredients, set aside. Combine the milk, banana, oil and egg and stir into the flour mixture until moist. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes into 1 gallon of water with 1 tablespoon salt dissolved in it.
Drain and wash well.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Cook sugar, syrup and water into syrup. Add butter.
Pour pineapple over potatoes, then syrup.
Cook on 350° for 35 minutes.

title: george washington cherry cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add beaten eggs and beat again.
Add soda and sour milk, then stir flour, spices and milk alternately to creamed mixture. Simmer cherries on stove and sweeten to taste.
Cool. Drain cherry juice off and add cherries, vanilla and nuts to the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: greek 'n rainbow twirls salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions, drain.
In large bowl, toss hot cooked pasta with cheese, olives and onion until well blended.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients, toss with pasta mixture until evenly coated.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and blueberries.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 cups hot water. Add fruit juices to total 4 cups liquid. Cool and add fruit. Refrigerate to congeal.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Wash tuna to remove salt.
Mix ingredients; pour in pie crust and top with pie crust.
Bake until golden brown.

title: chicken parmagiana
directions: Blend the Ricotta with salt, pepper and oregano.
In separate bowl, mix Ragu and tomatoes.
Rub chicken with garlic powder and brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons oil, approximately 12 minutes each side.
Remove and cool.
Place chicken in baking dish side by side.
Spoon 1/4 cup seasoned Ricotta mixture and 1/4 cup Ragu and tomato mixture in center of each breast.
Top each breast with 2 slices of Mozzarella and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: quick chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water 8 minutes; drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cooked spaghetti, cooked chicken, mushroom soup, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and mushrooms.
Stir in sour cream.
Transfer spaghetti mixture to a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup melted oleo, cheese, onion, sour cream, broccoli and soup.
Pour in greased casserole.
Combine remaining oleo to crushed cornflakes.
Pour over top casserole and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple pie with easy crust
directions: Note:
Sprinkle 3 teaspoons sugar on apples.

title: cheese dip
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature.
Chop olives, mushrooms, onion and dried beef.
Mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers.
Dip may be frozen.

title: filipino chicken soup
directions: Chop the chicken into pieces.
Put into a pot with the crushed ginger.
Cook, uncovered, until the liquid has evaporated.
Brown chicken slightly and add to the patis and enough water to cover the chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until the chicken is tender.
If you need more soup, add a can of chicken broth.
Add the vegetables of your choice.
Add the long rice for the last 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onion together about 5 minutes; drain.
Mix together the sour cream and soup; add to zucchini.
Mix melted butter in dressing.
Use half the dressing in bottom of large casserole.
Spoon on zucchini and top with remaining dressing. Bake about 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly and done.

title: chunky relish
directions: Cover vegetables with the water and salt.
Let set overnight. Drain vegetables.
Bring vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar to a boil.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal.
Put in water bath for 15 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook meat, onions and green pepper until meat is brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic powder; heat through.
Combine spaghetti, margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Press into a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over crust. Fill crust with meat mixture.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream together until light and fluffy the salad oil and sugar. Add well beaten eggs.
Sift flour before measuring and add it to the
spices and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, add it and the
dry mixture alternately to the egg, sugar and salad oil mixture.
Beat after each addition.
Lightly dredge the fruit and nuts
with	extra
flour
and
add.
Next,	add pineapple and jam. Stir to get good distribution.
Grease and flour 3 (8 or 9-inch) pans.
Fill and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Cut corn from cob and place in saucepan with whipping cream. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in salt, sugar and m.s.g.
Melt butter in a small pan and stir in flour; do not brown.
Stir butter and flour mixture into corn and cook until slightly thickened.
Turn corn into ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan and dot with butter.
Brown under browning unit.

title: sugar-free brownies
directions: Mix cocoa, melted shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix. Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake until top has dull crust, a slight imprint will be left when top is lightly touched with finger.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.
Temperature: 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold in strawberries and sugar.
Spread over cooled pie.
Refrigerate 4 hours or longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: waltenee chicken
directions: Put chicken parts in baking dish.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Pour dressing over pieces.
Dot with preserves.
Marinate at least 2 to 3 hours.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours depending on how tender the chicken is.
Also, baste occasionally and turn when one side is brown.
Serve on bed of rice or noodles.

title: mother's cheese loaf
directions: Either grind or put in food processor green pepper; drain and add cheese and grind.
Dissolve jello in hot water; while still warm, add cheese and stir until smooth.
Add pimentos, pecans, salt and red and green pepper.
Grease mold and chill until firm. Unmold to serve.

title: annie wingate's punch recipe
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a gallon container.
Pour into two half gallon containers.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer; crush.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 40.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine until blended well.
Add vanilla.
Knead until stiff to roll out with sugar.
Roll out thin, spread on peanut butter, roll up and slice into bite-size pieces.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together and press in pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: yankee-style maple syrup fudge
directions: Combine maple syrup, corn syrup and cream in a 2-quart heavy saucepan and place over low heat. Stir constantly until mixture begins to boil. Continue cooking, without stirring, to the soft-ball (236°) or until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a small ball that flattens when removed from the water. Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring or beating. Then beat with electric mixer on low speed until candy loses its gloss and thickens. This takes quite a while. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into lightly buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. When cool, cut in 21 pieces. Makes about 1 pound.

title: pre-k pm's rice krispie surprise!
directions: Set stove temperature.
Get big pot and put marshmallows in. Add candy (big hunk).
Next, add 2 gallons water, stir it up and add 5 apples.
Then nod head 5 times.
Add 1 banana and pour it into 3 small pots, then add 10 carrots.
Put black pepper in 1 pot. Rest and drink 1000 Cokes while cooking.
Pour rest of ingredients in and stir with Power Ranger Sword.
Must cook for 5 minutes.

title: chile
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer approximately 2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well; spread in large shallow pan.
Top with: lettuce, tomato, onions, green pepper, cheese and olives (optional). Serve with nacho chips.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese, soup, onion, pimento and sliced eggs together. Put asparagus in greased casserole dish.
Pour mixture over asparagus; top with cracker crumbs that have been put in melted oleo.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients in large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients well; add to wet ingredients a small amount at a time until mixed well. Cook in greased loaf or Bundt 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a Dutch oven, using olive oil, saute onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, basil, oregano, thyme, parsley, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cover the pot and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with favorite pasta.

title: vanilla butter cream frosting
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add salt and part of sugar gradually, blending after each addition.
Add egg and remaining sugar alternately with vanilla and milk until of right consistency to spread.
Makes enough for two 9-inch layers.

title: creamed peas and new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; remove a narrow strip of peel around center of each.
Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Cook peas and green onions in boiling salted water to cover 8 to 12 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine vegetables in a serving dish; set aside and keep warm.
Melt butter in a small heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened and is bubbly.
Stir in salt.
Pour mixture over vegetables, stirring to coat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and water to light syrupy stage and add oleo.
As soon as oleo is bubbling good, add peanuts.
When mixture reaches hard crack stage (305°), remove from heat and add soda.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into 2 pizza pans or 2 large cookie sheets that have been sprayed with Pam.
Level off candy with spoon to thickness of peanuts.
Set where it is cool.
(We use electric frypan set at 340° for cooking.)

title: date raisin bars(makes 12)
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine cereal, buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Let stand 3 minutes or until cereal is softened. Add dates and raisins.
Stir in flour mixture, mixing only until combined.
Spread butter evenly into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes clean.
Let cool, cut into 12 bars.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread into a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together; chill.

title: favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add remaining ingredients. Chill dough overnight (or freeze it until you're ready to bake). Roll out dough on floured surface until 1/4-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters. Place on ungreased sheet. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until just barely brown on edges. Cool and ice cookies. Enjoy! Makes 2 dozen big cookies!

title: squash casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed; spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook celery and onion in small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Mix with squash, celery and onion.
Spread on top of stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: orange date bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and mix well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in walnuts, dates and 1 tablespoon orange peel.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes, until done.

title: pineapple walnut drops cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg.
Stir in pineapple, walnuts and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients; stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: ritz crackers pie(just like apple pie)
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar and water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Drop in 20 Ritz crackers (do not break them up).
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into an unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: wild rice chickpea shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice with thyme added to water.
In large bowl, combine the cooked rice, shrimp, olives, chickpeas, onion and pimento. Pile into individual lettuce cups or serve in lettuce lined salad bowls.
Drizzle with lemon vinaigrette.
(Chickpeas and garbanzo beans are two names for the same thing.)
Yields 8 servings.

title: granny's easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in water and drain.
Arrange one layer of cooked macaroni and one of cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Sprinkle pepper on each layer.
Beat eggs, adding milk.
Salt as desired. Pour over layers.
Dot generously with margarine or butter.
Bake at 325° for about 45 to 60 minutes or until no longer soupy.

title: garlic wine sauce
directions: Combine the shallots, garlic, salt and pepper in a small nonreactive saucepan over high heat. Stir in the stock and the wine; bring to a boil. Cook over high heat for 15 minutes. Swirl in the butter; remove from the heat and continue to whisk in the butter until thoroughly incorporated. Serve immediately or prepare without the butter and store, refrigerated, in an airtight container for up to 24 hours. Reheat in a small saucepan over low heat. When the sauce comes to a simmer, swirl in the butter and proceed from there. Yield: 3/4 cup.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown beef and hot sausage.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, oregano, garlic salt and pepper. Put on party rye and broil.

title: rosemary coffee cake
directions: Mix biscuit mix, sugar, nutmeg, rosemary and lemon rind.
Beat egg and add to milk; add oil.
Stir liquid mixture into dry mixture just until batter is formed.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: taco pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Combine beef with taco seasoning mix and spread in a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds on high in a blender or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour milk mixture over beef in pie plate. Bake uncovered in a preheated 400° oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: patacones
directions: Choose several green plantains at the grocery store.
(If regular stores are out, you can usually fine them at a Latino market.
If they have started to yellow, they are too ripe for this recipe.
DO NOT USE BANANAS!

title: jezebel sauce(serve over cream cheese with crackers)
directions: Combine all and serve over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Thaw spinach. Make a white sauce. Melt butter. Blend in flour to make a smooth paste. Then stir in milk gradually, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and smooth. Add well-beaten eggs, spinach, sugar, salt and pepper. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli with other ingredients.
Place in lightly greased baking dish dotted with butter.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: fast and easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef lightly.
Drain off fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: hattie's old fashioned mincemeat
directions: Grind cooked meat and suet.
Chop fine or grind apples.
Mix all ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.
Then put immediately into jars and seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Place in heavy skillet. Beat egg yolks and gradually add the milk which has been slightly warmed.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly and cook over medium-low temperature until thickened.
Stir to prevent sticking. Cool and pour into prepared pie shell.
Top with meringue and slightly brown in 350° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: olive-nut sandwich spread
directions: Mash the soft cream cheese with a fork.
Add the mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

The spread will be slightly mushy, but after it is refrigerated for a few hours, it will be firmer and of spreading consistency. Besides making a delicious sandwich, this is great on toast or lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 servings.

title: jeanetta's apple pandowdy
directions: Fill a deep ovenproof dish with 8 cups thinly sliced apples. Sprinkle with apple cider, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, brown sugar and butter.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter, egg and sugar in large bowl; add potatoes. Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in small bowl.
Add alternately by hand with milk to potato mixture until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat slightly.
Add garlic salt.
Alternate layer of meat, potatoes, onions, salt and pepper and soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine pineapple and marshmallows and let set overnight.
Add Dream Whip, apple, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: crab mousse
directions: In double boiler, heat mushroom soup and cream cheese. Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 c. cold water.
Add to mushroom mixture and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients, chill in refrigerator in ring mold.

title: burgundy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch chunks.
Cut carrots into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Cut peeled potatoes into 2-inch chunks.
Coarsely chop onion.
In a nonstick 12-inch skillet on medium-high heat in 2 teaspoons hot olive oil, cook chicken until the juices run clear. Remove to a bowl.
In drippings, add 1 teaspoon olive oil; cook carrots, potatoes and onion until brown.
Stir in red wine; cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes, bouillon, thyme and 1 1/4 cups water. Bring to a boil on high heat; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: drunken black bean soup
directions: Wash, drain and pick through beans to remove stones and/or spoiled beans.
In a large stock pot, bring the chicken stock and beans to a boil.

In a medium size skillet or saute pan, saute the bacon with onion and garlic, until the bacon is lightly browned. Add to the beans and cook over medium heat for about 1 hour or until the beans are just tender and the stock has thickened.
Add the tomato paste, salt and pepper (be careful not to get the soup too salty; the bacon adds salt flavor as well).
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Stir in cilantro and beer and continue cooking 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
The soup should have an abundant amount of broth; be prepared to add more chicken stock or water if necessary.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix soups with 1/2 cup milk.
Heat.
Toss all ingredients together with spaghetti.
Pour soup over spaghetti.
Top with desired amount of grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Stir flour, sugar and baking soda together.
Cut in shortening until size of peas. Mix buttermilk with yeast water; add to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until moistened.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Sprinkle with flour; knead 4 to 5 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place close together on lightly greased pan. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Makes 20 to 24.

title: sweet 'n hot beans
directions: Fry bacon. Drain. Add onions and cayenne. Cook until tender. Stir in sugar and beans.
Simmer a few moments before serving. Great for a "patio" affair.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add avocados, lemon
juice and Bleu cheese mix.
Blend until smooth. Refrigerate.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday fruit punch(dutch recipe)
directions: This is a faster version of the Fruit and Wine appetizer.

title: bacardi double-chocolate rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, 1/2 cup of the water and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Using electric mixer, beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup of the chocolate pieces.
Pour batter into prepared greased 12-cup Bundt pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: asparagus casserole *
directions: Drain peas, add cheese and mushroom soup.
Cook until cheese melts.
In a casserole, put a layer of asparagus, sliced boiled eggs, soup mixture, almonds and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini and boil a few minutes in salted water; drain. Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover last 20 minutes of baking time.

title: company casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: citrus ginger chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well with a wire whisk.
Brush half of marmalade mixture evenly over chicken breast halves.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place rack on grill over medium-hot grill.

title: spaghetti
directions: Boil water. Put in spaghetti. Dice onion in boiling water and add butter. When spaghetti is soft, drain. Put cold spaghetti sauce and Ranch dressing on hot spaghetti.

title: stuffed peppers carolyn
directions: Place lentils in broth; bring to boil.
Add carrot; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Brown bacon until well done.
Dry on paper towels to remove excess grease; crumble.
Saute onions in oil until golden brown.
Combine with bacon, lentils, egg, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and half of the cheese. Cut tops off peppers (about 1 inch), removing seeds and pulp.
Fill with lentil mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Place in a covered casserole.
Pour remaining sauce in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Beat egg in bowl.
Add milk, sugar, melted butter, vanilla and cinnamon.
Grease casserole bowl or spray with Pam.
Crumble biscuits (these work best) or bread into milk mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° to 375° until tester comes clean.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Pour into punch bowl over cake of ice.
Add ginger ale.

title: molded spinach salad(yield:  1 quart)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
When Jell-O is dissolved, add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add vinegar, salt and mayonnaise.
Blend with electric mixer until well mixed.
Refrigerate until soft set. Beat again until Jell-O mixture is fluffy.
Fold in finely chopped raw spinach, diced celery and chopped onion.
Pour into 1-quart well oiled mold and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold and top with 1 cup cottage cheese.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Pound chicken; spread with 1 tablespoon dressing.
Place 1/2 of cheese over dressing.
Roll up and place in baking dish. Combine sauerkraut, celery seed, caraway seed, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Cover chicken with sauerkraut mixture, then cover with remaining dressing and cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 2.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Flatten Pillsbury crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
After done baking, spread Miracle Whip, cream cheese and dressing mixture over crescent.
Top with shredded cheese or any vegetable you choose.

title: pierogis
directions: Heat potatoes.
Roll out dough; cut with glass and fill. Pinch edges with fork and drop if not freezing into boiling water until they come to the top and brown in skillet with onion and butter.

title: egg mcburross
directions: Spray custard bowl or coffee cup with Pam, then crack egg into custard bowl or coffee cup.
Break yolk and cover with plastic wrap.
Poke holes on top of plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave for 60 seconds (may vary with each microwave).
Butter English muffin and toast in toaster oven.
Then place cheese on one slice of English muffin and heat in microwave until melted.
Then place egg and ham (or meat of your preference) on cheese and then place other side of muffin on that.
Spread teaspoon of mayonnaise on muffin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Eat and enjoy!

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 225°. In large saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Heat until boiling. Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda. Stir until mixture foams. Pour over popped corn and stir well to coat.

title: cottage cheese-orange jello salad
directions: Blend dry jello and cottage cheese until smooth and colored even and other ingredients one at a time.
Let set 2 hours in refrigerator and serve.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Cook noodles.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan; stir to mix.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken delight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.

title: sugar crisp cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Roll in balls and dip in water, then sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes or until done, but not browned.
Tops will crinkle.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Brown ribs in skillet in small amount of oil.
Layer ribs in baking dish.
Drain grease from skillet.
In same skillet, simmer the onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add catsup, water, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Simmer until it thickens.
Pour over ribs in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Use sauce as gravy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Place 1/2 in bottom of pan (or dish).
Place chicken in bite size pieces on stuffing.
Mix soup and 1 can of chicken broth together and pour over chicken.
Put rest of stuffing on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: peppermint eggnog punch
directions: Combine eggnog and ice cream.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale slowly.
You can use small candy canes as stirrers in each cup.
Makes about 24 punch cups.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in well-greased pan (buttered) and refrigerate 1 hour before eating.

title: crab melts
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat; add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt and mix well.
Process in blender until smooth.
In bowl, fold in crabmeat and pimientos and mix well.
Slice bread into 1/2-inch slices and spread on crabmeat mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 20 slices.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then all the rest.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.

title: lillie mae's north carolina barbecue
directions: In a stainless steel or enameled kettle, combine meat, vinegar, vegetables, garlic and peppercorns.
Add just enough water to cover meat.
Bring the liquid to a boil over moderately high heat, skimming the froth as it rises to the surface.
Simmer the pork, partially covered, for 2 hours or until tender.
Make tomato barbecue sauce.

title: ham and dill party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Chill overnight.
Cut out center of bread and use as bowl for dip.
Cut different types of bread into small squares to use for dipping.
I usually use pumpernickel, wheat and sourdough.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Peel peaches and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mash peaches and add.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 1/2 gallon of ice cream.

title: gallon salad
directions: Mix all together and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: cool cucumber dip
directions: In medium bowl stir mayonnaise and yogurt until blended.
Stir in cucumber, onion and dill.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups, 20 calories per tablespoon.

title: gringo casserole
directions: Mix taco seasoning with hamburger.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish in order listed.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy hominy casserole
directions: Cook hominy in liquid for 20 minutes.
Drain juice from hominy and save.
Mix soup, shredded cheese, some of the juice from hominy and dash of salt and pepper.
Crumble crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening.
Add to mixture, then add sugars gradually.
Beat until light.
Combine coconut and cornflakes with mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until delicately browned.
Makes 4 dozen.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Cover and set in refrigerator 4 hours. Then spoon batter into greased cupcake pan or muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in very large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Batter can be kept in refrigerator up to 6 weeks. To bake, spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: sugar-free hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended. Store in an airtight container.
Use 4 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of boiling water.
Stir.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix together the buttermilk, vanilla and soda; add to the creamed mixture.
Add baking powder, salt and flour; mix all together with mixer or large wooden spoon.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture before baking.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate until set.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool.
Drain pineapple and use juice to soften cheese.
Beat until creamy.
Add cheese, pineapple, pecans and 7-Up to jello.
Let chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a deep-dish pan or heavy pottery and melt in the preheating oven.
Mix remaining ingredients except blackberries into a smooth batter.
Pour batter over melted
butter but do not stir.
Place blackberries, or desired fruit, over the batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Bake 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix in a 1-gallon container; fill with water.
For added zing, place in a large container and add 1 liter of Sprite or ginger ale.
Can add sherbet.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add to hot milk, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened in double boiler. Divide mixture in half.
To first half, add 1 cup chocolate chips while hot.
When chocolate chips are dissolved, pour into baked pie shell.
Add to 2nd half of mixture, gelatin that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Fold well beaten egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour this mixture over chocolate mixture filling in pie shell.
Sprinkle with grated unsweetened chocolate.
Chill and serve.
Have pie shell cooked and cooled before starting pie.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Add 2/3 cup sugar and beat in slowly until stiff.
Add salt, vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips and stir in.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on foil.
Put in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave overnight.
Food coloring can be added (at Christmas, green coloring and red sprinkles).

title: cranberry brie
directions: Peel off top rind of Brie cheese round, leaving 1/4-inch rim. Combine all other ingredients, except pecans.
Top cheese with mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Beat egg.
Add noodles, raisins, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° until knife in center comes out clean.
Sometimes I add chopped nuts when mixing.

title: shrimp cocktail with tangy dip
directions: Boil shrimp and drain.
Cook for approximately 3 to 5 minutes. Cool and refrigerate.

title: hot cider
directions: Tie spices into a small cloth bag.
Simmer cider and spices for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove spices.
Serve hot.

title: cheesy potato beef bake
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook Beef until no longer pink, drained.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Top with Mushrooms.
Combine Potatoes and contents of sauce mix packets, Milk, Water, Butter, Salt, Seasoned Salt, and Pepper.
Pour over beef and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with Cheese; bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt belle's squash patties
directions: Mix all together.
Drop from spoon into deep hot fat.
Cook until brown.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut lengthwise into thick pieces.
Cook in salted boiling water for 7 minutes.
Drain and arrange in single layer to dry.
Heat 1 inch oil in large, heavy skillet.
Fry about 7 minutes.
Drain and season with salt and pepper.

title: trish's cherry dessert
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in small bowl or mixer.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Add sugar alternately with sour cream and vanilla, beating until mixture is spreading consistency.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Fry in a little oil until golden brown.

title: toasted ravioli appetizers
directions: In heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, heat 1-inch vegetable oil (approximately 2 cups). Dip ravioli into eggs. Coat with seasoned bread crumbs. Deep fry ravioli in small batches for 1 minute or until golden brown. Remove with slotted spoon. Drain on paper towels.
Yields 8 appetizer servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and mix with celery, onion and almonds.
Mix last 5 ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Marinate for several hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine gelatine and cold water; set aside.
Slightly beat egg yolks.
Mix all together and cook in double boiler until thick. Add gelatine to cooked mixture and chill.
Chill and add egg whites, beaten.
When it begins to set, add sugar and salt and fold all together and put in pie shell and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: jiffy corn bread bake
directions: Mix together.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil. Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Combine these two together. Add coconut, apples, nuts and vanilla. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Make holes in cake for icing.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Tastes best if refrigerated a few hours before serving.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking dish to 400°.
Partially bake crust 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks (slightly beaten), flour and milk.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened. Cool.
Add vanilla flavoring and mix.
Add sliced bananas to batter.
Line bottom of dish with crushed vanilla wafers about 1/2-inch thick.
Place wafers all around sides of dish.
Pour mixture into dish and top with meringue.

title: greek spinach dip
directions: Place spinach in a sieve;
press out as much liquid as possible.

title: poulet de normandie
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together lightly.
Put half of mixture in a buttered 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix the next 5 ingredients.
Put over bread mixture in casserole.
Top with remaining bread mixture.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over casserole. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix together oats and buttermilk.
Beat in sifted dry ingredients; add beaten eggs.
Bake on greased griddle and serve with favorite toppings.
Makes 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix
ingredients
in
large pot and let come to a boil. Boil 10	minutes
on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
For thicker jam, let boil a few minutes longer.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 pints.
Keeps in refrigerator for several months.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple and eggs.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add mixture to pineapple.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Toss bread cubes into melted margarine.
Place cubes on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good side dish for ham or pork chops.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add chili powder, corn, tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and cover with cornbread mix.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When serving, invert each helping.

title: better than luv cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and pour in 9 x 11-inch greased casserole dish.
While cake is cooking, in a small saucepan mix 1 can pineapple and sugar.
Mix until sugar dissolves; let cool.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Combine tomato juice, water and cabbage in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil, then simmer, uncovered, until cabbage is tender. Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Keeps for a week in refrigerator.
Serves 6.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil tomatoes for 2 to 3 minutes; rinse with cold water and remove peels.
Boil peeled tomatoes, vinegar and 1/2 cup water for 1 hour or until desired softness.
Mash tomatoes; add onion and jalapenos and spices.
Pour in pint jars and seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour together in pan. Blend milk and eggs yolks together and blend into dry ingredients until smooth. Cook over medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla, stirring well until mixed. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: cherry jazz
directions: Spread cherry
pie
filling in bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square baking
pan.
Sprinkle
dry
cake mix over pie filling. Pour melted butter
over
cake
mix.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm.

title: layered dessert
directions: Blend flour, 3/4 cup chopped nuts and margarine in mixer.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Whip together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip; spread over first layer.
Mix pudding according to package, using only 3 cups milk.
Spread over second layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: granny alice henry's crumb cakes
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients and set aside about 1 1/2 cups of this mixture to use for crumb topping.
To the remaining mixture, add the last 4 ingredients.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch cake pans and sprinkle with the reserved crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southern grilled pork loin
directions: Take 1 pork loin and put on generous portion of Worcestershire sauce on all sides.
Put seasoned pepper on all sides.
Wrap in aluminum foil and put on grill on low temperature.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours or until done.
Turn several times during cooking.
Slice and serve.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Mix together rice, pineapple, sugar and vanilla.
Cool.
Add whipped cream.
Mix.
Chill.
Before serving, add 1/4 pound white or colored marshmallows.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Add 2 cups flour; mix well.
Add 2 more cups flour; let rise for 1 hour or may refrigerate overnight.

title: new orleans remoulade dressing
directions: Chop ingredients down to egg medium fine.
Cut egg in small chunks.
Mix with all other ingredients.
If so desired, you may mix anchovy paste for taste.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Mix together butter and sugar. Mix it well. Beat in eggs one at a time. Gradually mix in oil, vanilla and flour. When thoroughly mixed, fold in the Rice Krispies. Drop 1 tablespoon of dough at a time on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, then pour over meat and marinate in refrigerator, covered, for 1 hour or if you don't have the time, it's just as good to cook immediately on grill or in oven.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour for thin sliced pork chops.
If substituting other meats, cook as usual.

title: coconut-pineapple custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl and then pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake a 350° about 45 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put together in a bottle or cruet.
Shake and chill.
Will last a long time.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to measure 1 cup.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk mixture and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Drop batter from tablespoon into deep, hot fat (375°).

title: german slaw
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar, celery seed, dry mustard and salt.
Boil and pour over first 3 ingredients.
Store in icebox.
Use as needed.

title: corn flake crunch
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar and Karo syrup and bring to a boil. Remove instantly and pour over cornflakes and stir.
Spray Pam in pan and spread evenly.

title: celery frittata
directions: Cook celery and onions until tender.
Reserve juice.
In mixing bowl, add celery, onions, eggs, salt, a dash of pepper and Bisquick.
Add juice to make a medium batter.
Drop by tablespoon in skillet that has about 1/2-inch of oil.

title: caramel corn
directions: Grease the sides and bottom of a large pan with butter.
Add the 3 quarts of popped corn and set aside.
In a heavy pan, combine the white sugar, butter or margarine, brown sugar, Karo syrup and pecans.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes after it starts to boil or to 300° on a candy thermometer.
Pour over popped corn and toss.
Turn out on a greased cookie sheet; cool and break into pieces.

title: mary's hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble Tostitos chips up; spread over bottom of baking dish. Brown ground chuck; drain.
Mix together ground chuck, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups and tomato sauce or salsa. Pour mixture over chips.
Use two kinds of cheese and sprinkle over the top of casserole.

title: brown sugar peanut brittle
directions: Butter two 15 x 10 x 1-inch pans or 2 cookie sheets; set aside.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine the sugars, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook and stir until the sugars dissolve. Continue cooking until the mixture boils.
Stir in the butter or margarine.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Continue cooking, without stirring to 230°.
Cook and stir to 280°.
Stir in the peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 300°.
Remove pan from heat.
Quickly stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour onto pans, shaking until evenly spread.
Break candy into pieces when cool. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add bananas and eggs. Add sour milk. Gradually add flour and soda to mixture. Add pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger and noodle casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and onion until browned.
Season and add undiluted tomato soup.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water. Melt butter.
Break bread in small pieces and brown lightly in butter.
Place hamburger on large platter or casserole.
Drain noodles and place them on top of hamburger.
Top with bread crumbs.
Serves 4 people.

title: gnocchi milanaise(boiled)
directions: This dish should be prepared just when ready to serve, least the gnocchis toughen.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Crumble and brown ground meat in skillet.
Put ground meat in casserole dish.
Slice cheese and lay solid over the meat.
Put soup over the cheese (do not use any water in soup).
Place Tater Tots to cover the top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: toasted tuna tantalizers
directions: Mix the
tuna,	eggs,
cheese,	onions,
pickle,
green pepper, mayonnaise, salt
and pepper together and put on split buns.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil until cheese melts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all but last 3 ingredients; cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes until heated, stirring once.
Mix in lettuce and grapes; sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 4.

title: mary's carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash. Add butter, milk and beaten eggs.
Fold in grated cheese last. Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spanish cream
directions: Soften gelatine in cold milk in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir until gelatine and sugar are thoroughly dissolved.
Slowly pour small amount of hot mixture over slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return to double boiler and cook over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Fold gelatine mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Chill until firm. (This will separate and form a jelly on the bottom and a custard on top.)
Serve with whipped cream, sliced oranges or any fruit you like.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix altogether in a 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 75 minutes.
Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Saute onion and bell peppers in margarine.
Add soup, broth, chilies, taco sauce, and chicken.
Cook 20 minutes, slowly.
Layer tortillas, meat, and cheese.
Repeat. Heat at 350° for about 25 minutes.
May be fixed early and frozen.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pie filling and undrained pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Split zucchini in half and cook in salted water until just soft.
Drain and cool slightly.
In a saucepan combine butter, onion, celery, water and bouillon cube; boil until onion is translucent.
Scoop pulp out of zucchini, leaving shell intact. Salt and pepper shell before stuffing.
Combine together zucchini pulp (cut into small pieces), onion liquid mixture, seasoned bread crumbs (may need more crumbs, depends on size of zucchini) and Cheddar cheese.
Add extra seasonings, if desired.
Bake in oven about 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with remaining shredded Cheddar cheese or Mozzarella may be used for topping. Bake until cheese has melted.

title: grandma's sour cream raisin pie(makes two 8-inch or 9-inch pies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook raisins in a small amount of water until plump.
Drain off liquid. Stir together the raisins, sugar, sour cream, beaten eggs, vanilla and margarine.
Pour into two unbaked pie crusts.
Cover with top crusts and crimp edges.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until crusts are brown.

title: dish of plenty
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine all and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in saucepan; heat until it bubbles around edge.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread on top of Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: onion pie(servings: 8)
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in shortening and warm water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place dough in a lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let dough rise in a warm place for 1/2 hour.
Pat dough into a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan or onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Press up edges to make a slight rim.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove from grease and drain on absorbent paper.
Add onions to bacon grease, cook slowly until tender, but not brown.
Sprinkle onion, bacon, cumin, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper over dough. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Blend egg yolk and sour cream.
Pour over onions.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until golden brown and sour cream is set.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: bobbie schonaerts english almond toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar, water and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until it boils.
Cook without stirring to 236 degrees (soft ball).
Add almonds, and continue cooking to 290 degrees (hard crack), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Mixture changes to deep caramel color.
Stir in soda.
Turn out onto greased baking sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness. Immediately spread with chocolate, spread chocolate over candy as it melts.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Cool, break into pieces.

title: easy torte
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Cool.
Split layers horizontally.

title: captain chuck's cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter and mix together with flour, sugar, salt, milk and yeast.
Knead well and let sit until yeast is active.
Roll flat and cover surface with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll flat dough into a log with cinnamon and sugar on the inside.
Cut log roll into round pieces.
Lay pieces on their sides on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned on top.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix pineapple juice and pudding mix.
Fold in fruit (except banana) and chill.
Just before serving, stir in the sliced banana and nuts.

title: lush
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix and beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread on top of cooled crust.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion together.
In a dish, layer the chips, meat mixture, 1 can beans and cheese.
Make second layer of each.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel together; pour over the top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Add spices to sauce.
Saute onion, garlic and pepper (chopped) until tender.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Butter large casserole dish.
Heat oven to 375°.
Slice cheese into sandwich slices.
Place one layer of noodles in bottom of casserole dish.
Lightly spread over sauce then add a layer of cheese.
Repeat this step two more times.
Cheese should be on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chip beef cheese ball
directions: Snip 3/4 package of beef finely. Cream the beef with the cheese, seasonings and onions. Form into ball and roll in remaining beef that has been snipped fine. Chill and serve.

title: bacardi rum punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale or 7-Up, in a punch bowl.
Add plenty of ice and stir.
Add the ginger ale or 7-Up. Serves 18 people.

title: angel flake biscuits
