directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix with buttermilk. Sift flour and sugar together. Mix all ingredients as you would regular biscuits. (Can keep in refrigerator for days.) Roll and let stand 10 to 15
minutes. Bake on ungreased baking sheet in very hot oven (450°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash, hull and sort berries, saving perfect berries for placing in crust.
Crush enough berries to make 1 cup (about half of berries).
Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch, crushed berries and water.
Cook over direct flame until thickened.
Add few drops of red food coloring and cool thoroughly.
Just before serving, place whole berries in cooled crust.
Pour cooked sauce over berries. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in oblong 1-quart casserole.
Add peas. Combine cream of mushroom soup, milk, green pepper and onion. Pour over peas.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add the persimmon puree and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the persimmon mixture. Beat well.
Pour into a greased baking pan and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: appetizer
directions: Thaw sprouts and cook minimum amount of time.
Drain.
Put in a flat dish (like a loaf baking dish) and pour the pickle juice over them.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, spoon juice over them again.
When ready to serve, drain and serve with toothpicks.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies and pie filling according to directions or use prepared brownies and chocolate mousse.
Use a large glass bowl or trifle dish.
Put a layer of broken up brownies, next a layer of chocolate pie filling, next a layer of candy bars (broken in pieces) then a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers again and sprinkle candy bar pieces on top of Cool Whip.
Serves up to 24 people or one serious chocoholic!!!

title: pumpkin mousse pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box with 3/4 cup of milk. Blend in pumpkin, spice and 2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Spread with remaining whipped topping.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla. Beat at low speed until light. Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy. Add milk to make of spreading consistency. Frosts one 8 or 9-inch square cake.

title: scalloped potatoes(enough for an electric roaster)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Fry onions in butter, add flour and seasoning and gradually add milk to make a sauce, stirring all the time.
When thickened, pour over potatoes and ham in roaster.
Bake at least 2 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: apple-pineapple dessert
directions: *Artificial sweetener can be used to equal 1/2 cup sugar, if desired.

title: elsie's egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla to scalded milk.
Add eggs last.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg (lightly).
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until knife test.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Pour water in large mixing bowl, add yeast and let stand a few minutes; stir to dissolve.
Add 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, egg and shortening.
Beat until smooth, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Then add rest of the flour, mix and scrape sides of the bowl.
Cover, let rise until double in size, about 30 minutes.
Grease muffin pans, spoon in batter, filling about half full.
Let rise until they reach top of muffin cups.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; add relish and hamburger.
Serve with corn chips.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in Crisco.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend well.
Dough is ready to be refrigerated or made into biscuits. Turn dough onto floured counter and knead lightly.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise slightly.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Melt chocolate and shortening.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt gradually.
Add flour to egg mixture, then add chocolate and melted shortening.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake about 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: col. sanders' chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Make meringue of egg whites stiffly beaten, with equal amount of sugar and small amount of nutmeg; brown.
(Equal amounts means equal measure of sugar and egg whites.)

title: supper tarts
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add cabbage, onion, sauce, salt, pepper, etc.
Cook until cabbage and onion are tender.
Roll dough.
Fill with mixture.
Bake or fry.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together with mixer for few minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and top with topping.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk and beat with mixer.
Add dry ingredients and beat well with mixer.
Stir in zucchini last by hand.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: friday spanish rice
directions: In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, add ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring at first.
Serves 4.

title: maple oat chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease the cookie sheets.
Cream the sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add molasses and eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in oats and Rice Krispies.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from sheet.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Mix with all ingredients and pour in oblong casserole.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine, sugar and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs; beat.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices; add to creamed mixture (will be quite stiff).
Add apples and nuts.
Mix by hand.
Bake in rectangular pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick 'n' easy chili con queso
directions: Cut Velveeta into cubes.
Place in microwave-safe bowl (Rubbermaid not recommended).
Pour salsa over top of cheese. Cover bowl with paper towel.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Flour and salt pork chops.
Place a small amount of shortening in a skillet and fry pork chops until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over browned pork chops.
Cook at 260° to 280° for 1 hour.
It may be necessary to add water to mixture while it is simmering.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
If not thick enough, add a little flour.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: oven baked pork chops
directions: Set oven to 425°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; place in the oven for about 3 minutes or until butter melts. Stir together egg and milk.
Dip pork chops into egg mixture. Coat with stuffing mix.
Place chops atop melted butter in pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Turn chops over.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until chops are no longer pink.
Serve with apple slices or applesauce, if desired.

title: raisin cake *
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup and melted butter or margarine together.
Sift flour, allspice, baking powder and salt together in mixture.
Batter will be kind of stiff.
Add a box of raisins, one at a time, and mix well.
Use a 9-inch spout pan.
Line bottom of pan with paper and grease well.
Cook in heated oven at 250° for 2 hours and 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture. Combine rest of sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Roll dough into balls and roll in sugar mixture.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: bell house anchovy salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients, except eggs and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well and add salad oil, 1/4 cup at a time.
Makes 1 quart of dressing.

title: boiled country ham in pressure cooker
directions: Use pressure cooker with rack in it.
If ham has hard skin, soak 1 hour in water to cover.
Tenderized ham does not require soaking.
Place ham on rack and water in cooker.
Exhaust cooker. Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 15 pounds pressure.
Let indicator return to 0.

title: deluxe honey pecan chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes and pecans in large bowl; set aside. Stir mayonnaise, sour cream, honey, poppy seed and pepper in small bowl to blend well and add to chicken mixture.
Toss well to coat. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato, green bean salad
directions: Place all ingredients, except green beans and potatoes, in shaker or bag and shake well.
Pour over vegetables and toss gently.
Chill several hours.

title: apple pie with crumb topping
directions: Fill uncooked pie shells with sliced apples.
Mix flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon and crumble on top of pies.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda
and salt.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extracts.
Mix all
together.
Add fruit cocktail.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top
with
1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts. Sprinkle cinnamon
over
top.
Bake
hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping.
Serves 9 to 10.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove garlic.
Season to taste.
Serve with hot rice. Serves 8 to 12.

title: potato burgers
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Make into patties.
Roll in flour. Fry in pan with melted butter or oil.
After brown on both sides, put on a cover to make sure potatoes get done.

title: drunken wieners
directions: In large saucepan, mix bourbon, sugar, catsup, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add frankfurters and simmer for 40 minutes. Serve in chafing dish.
May be prepared ahead.
Serves 20.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip well; add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Stir in sugar, half the flour and the salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in the rest of the flour until smooth.
Cover with a cloth and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes or until dough is double in size.
Grease 12 large muffin cups.
Stir down the dough.
Spoon dough into muffin cups, filling them half full. Allow to rise for 30 minutes.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat unit until margarine and mustard are dissolved.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: Saute garlic and sweet basil in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes, then add chickpeas.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Cook any kind of small macaroni separately.
Drain macaroni and add to soup mixture.
Serve with Romano or Parmesan cheese.

title: hopping john
directions: Saute ham, onion and hot pepper sauce in oil over moderate heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until onion is soft but not browned. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Serves 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Heat in 350° oven until warm or brown on top.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: church salad
directions: Mix all together, then refrigerate.

title: two layer cheese cake(low-fat version)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and egg with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour in crust and bake 25 minutes.
Blend sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla, pour over first layer and return to the oven.
Bake another 15 minutes. Chill and serve.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Sift flour, soda, ginger and salt; set aside.
Heat the molasses and butter until lukewarm.
Pour in buttermilk and slightly beaten egg.
Beat thoroughly.
Add the raisins and nuts to flour mixture and stir in molasses only until blended.
Drop into buttered muffin pans, 3/4 full.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar (1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar).
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini-shrimp canapes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Arrange zucchini slices on a serving platter.
Top each slice with 1 teaspoon of a chilled mixture.
Top each canape with 1 shrimp.
Garnish with dill sprigs, if desired.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into dish with butter (extra) on the bottom of dish.
Put Ritz cracker (crumb on top).
No changes.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried chicken kiev
directions: Brush each breast with lemon juice.
Put 3/4-inch cube butter on each piece.
Sprinkle with onion.
Fold and fasten with toothpicks.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix egg and milk and roll pieces in it.
Dip in cracker crumbs.
Chill 1 hour.
Cook in butter.
Cook first side 10 to 12 minutes, second side 5 to 7 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: boursin(herb cheese spread)
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand or food processor. Can store in air tight container in fridge for up to one month. Tastes better next day.
Makes great filling for rolled stuffed chicken breasts.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Mix and shape patties.
Wrap bacon around (close bacon ends with toothpick).
Broil until well done.
Yield: 6 patties.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pan spray small casserole.
Rinse and drain salmon.
Remove bones.
Heat milk and crumble bread into it. Stir.
Stir in salt and salmon.
Beat egg white until stiff; fold into salmon mixture.
Pour into casserole and bake 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato and onion. Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with tomatoes and onions. Can be served with crackers. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: donna's horseradish cheese ball
directions: Have horseradish and cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend all ingredients and shape in a ball. Cover with shredded dried beef (shred with scissors).

title: healthy granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients well; mix together the water, oil, vanilla (and honey, if used) and add to the dry ingredients.
Bake in a large 10 x 14-inch loaf cake pan in 275° oven for 1 hour. Stir every 20 minutes.
Add the raisins and dates last 20 minutes.

title: caramel grahams
directions: Whether received as gifts or nurtured from scratch, brandied fruit starters are making their way into thousands of Southern kitchens.
Our Brandied Fruit Starter can be served atop pound cake or ice cream and used to bake our Friendship Cake (recipe follows).
The starter should last indefinitely if handled properly.
Use clean equipment and keep it covered.

title: english muffin loaves(microwave)
directions: Combine 3 cups flour and the rest of the dry ingredients. Heat liquids in microwave oven to 125°.
Add heated liquids to dry mixture and beat well.
Stir in the rest of the flour (1 1/2 to 2 cups) to make a thick batter.
Pour into 2 glass loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops of dough with cornmeal and cover.
Let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Microwave each loaf on High power for 6 1/2 minutes (no longer).
Turn a half of turn after 3 minutes.
Surface of loaf will be moist, flat and pale in color.
Allow to rest 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Slice thin and toast.

title: fish chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, water, onions, carrots, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes, then stir in fish.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in 4 cups of milk and evaporated milk until smooth.
Blend remaining milk with flour and stir into chowder.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Garnish with parsley before serving.
Serves 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter; add remaining ingredients except cheese and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.
Ten minutes before done, add cheese and complete baking.

title: spinach and red leaf lettuce salad
directions: Combine lettuce and spinach and place on chilled salad plates.
Drizzle lightly with ribbon of vinaigrette.
Divide cashews, onion and pear among the plates.
Pass remaining vinaigrette dressing at table.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican layer casserole
directions: Brown beef (drain).
Add onions, taco seasoning, garlic powder, salt, pepper and picante sauce.
Mix well and let simmer about 5 minutes.
Layer casserole with chips, meat mixture, corn, beans and chili.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: wiener bits
directions: Cut wieners into bite sized pieces; mix together with other ingredients.
Heat in crock-pot on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: aunt sue's coconut cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 3 floured pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix cake mix (reserve 1 cup for topping) with 1/2 cup margarine and 1 egg.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: kentucky executive mansion's hello dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add graham cracker crumbs to melted butter.
Press evenly in bottom of dish.
Layer chocolate chips, coconut flakes, chopped nuts and sweetened condensed milk.
Bake in a preheated oven for 30 minutes or until edge turns slightly brown.
Makes 24 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Before baking, sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan at 350°.

title: ham casserole
directions: Chop ham.
In separate bowl mix soup and milk together and add ham.
Cook noodles as directed, drain and add to mixture. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake for 30 to 40 minutes on 375°.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cookies for kids
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls size of extra big marbles. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until brown around edge.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: In large covered dish, put layer of chops and onions, chops and onions. Keep alternating and cover with soy sauce to the top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook next day on grill.

title: herbal flea treatment
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a 1-pint bowl.
Open a seam of your pet's bedding item and insert the herbs.
Re-sew the seam. The herbs should repel fleas.
Yields 1 cup.

title: auntie jo jo's pastiera
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Pour into pie plate (8 or 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar. Mix well until thoroughly blended. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Roll dough into balls, 1 1/4-inches in diameter. Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until cookies are set, but not brown. Let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack; cool slightly. Roll on sugar while still warm. Cool completely. Freezes well.

title: dressing for crock-pot
directions: Cook celery a little before adding to other ingredients. Combine all ingredients.
Cook on high 45 minutes.
Cook on low 4 to 5 hours.

title: tossed potato salad
directions: Pour dressing over potatoes. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients and lightly mix together. Serves 8. Contains 75 calories.

title: bow tie pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Put ingredients in large bowl.
Toss until all are mixed and covered.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken breasts with wine
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter 15 minutes.
Arrange chicken in shallow roasting pan.
In same skillet, combine soup and wine; stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling point.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: breakfast tortillas
directions: In a small bowl, mix together beans and salsa.
Place a medium non-stick skillet over medium heat.
Pour beaten eggs into pan and allow bottom to set, approximately 1 minute.
Spread bean mixture onto one half of eggs and flip other half over to make a half circle.
Continue to cook until eggs are set.

title: poor man's german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, buttermilk, oil and soda together and beat until smooth.
Bake in 3 layers for 25 minutes in 350° oven. Remove from oven and cool.

title: indian tacos
directions: Mix ingredients well, forming a mixture like biscuit dough. Roll into circles about the size of a dinner plate (1/4-inch thick).
Deep fry until golden or cook in skillet.
Oil should be hot (about 350°).
Cooked bread is about 3/4 inch thick.

title: chicken overnight
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch shallow pan.
Cover for first part of baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: noodles(heritage recipe)
directions: Roll dough very thin.
Roll like jellyroll, cut in thin strips.
Shake out on board or table to dry.
Maybe cooked fresh or dry.
Can be frozen.

title: double chocolate truffles
directions: In a small saucepan, combine whipping cream and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until the mixture is very hot.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, chocolate bar pieces and liqueur.
Stir with whisk until smooth. Press plastic wrap directly onto surface; cool several hours or until mixture is firm enough to handle.

title: tennessee torte
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Fluff and butter together over low heat.
Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Press this over the bottom of the pie shell.
Pour over this the vanilla pudding and cherry pie filling mixed together into a marble effect.
Cool in refrigerator.
Sprinkle with crumbs.

title: cheese cake
directions: Add 1 egg and oil to cake mix.
Mix well (will be dry).
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar. Add 3 eggs and rest of the cake mix.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Pour into crust and bake 55 minutes at 325°.
When cool, top with cherry pie filling and Cool Whip before serving, if desired.

title: breakfast before
directions: Cook sausage.
Beat eggs. Add milk, mustard and salt.
Layer bread, sausage and eggs.
Add cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine sugar, salt, shortening and milk.
Set aside. Combine eggs, milk, yeast (dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water).
Add 6 cups flour.
Mix all together; let rise until double.
Punch down and knead.
Shape into rolls.	Let rise again in pan that has been well greased.	Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: Bring sugar and butter to a boil; boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Place graham crackers on cookie sheet as close as possible.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Pour sugar and butter mixture over graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes only at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and pat into long cake pan.
Brown in 400° oven; let cool.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving a 1 cup chocolate chips and the nuts.
Mix well and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onion in microwave dish.
Cover with plastic wrap; cook for 3 to 4 minutes only.
In medium bowl, pour milk, cheese, soup and 1/2 stick melted butter or oleo.
Stir together. Sprinkle salt and pepper in soup mixture and pour over potatoes. Add grated Cheddar cheese.
Re-cover with plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini and onions in pan, cover with water and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix the soup and sour cream; add to onions and zucchini.
Mix stuffing with the melted margarine.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with 2/3 of the stuffing mix.
Add the zucchini and onions; cover with the remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meal in one
directions: Place sliced potatoes in bottom of baking dish. Slice onions over potatoes. Spread hamburger over onions. Pour soup over top. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Soak bread in water 2 to 3 minutes, then squeeze out moisture. Combine soaked bread with remaining ingredients, mixing well. Form into small balls (about 20).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Add to spaghetti sauce; continue cooking for about 30 minutes more.

title: strawberry danish dessert
directions: Mix Danish dessert and cool.
Pinch off angel food cake into pieces, making 1 layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fix Dream Whip; add 1 1/3 cups of sugar and cream cheese.
Mix
all white mixtures together.
Mix strawberries in cooled Danish dessert.
Put following layers in pan:
layer of cake, white mixture and strawberry mixture.

title: marinated carrots - copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots for 20 minutes; drain. Mix remaining ingredients. Cut carrots and mix all. Best served at room temperature. Travels well to picnics, etc.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together and dip.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: liver and onions
directions: Soak liver 30 minutes before cooking in salt water.
Rinse well.
Dip in flour and place in iron skillet which has been preheated with shortening.
Brown on both sides.
Add slices of onion to top of liver and pour 3 cups of water over.
Turn heat to simmer liver and onions; cook until onions are done and you have a good thick brown gravy.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until very brown.
Remove and drain.
Brown onions slightly.
Add sugar, vinegar and flour to the grease.
Mix well. Gradually stir in water.
Cook until mixture thickens slightly, but is not stiff.
Pour over potatoes and crumbled bacon.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add water, bouillon, cauliflower and spices.
Cook.
Just before serving, add noodles and cook until they're tender.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Add milk when done and serve.
(This soup is best when served freshly made.)

title: lovelite 2 egg chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate 2 eggs and beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Stir into bowl 1 cup sugar, cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour in Wesson oil, milk and vanilla. Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add another 1/2 cup milk and egg yolks.
Beat 1 minute.
Fold in meringue and mixture into batter. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: molasses coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or when knife comes out clean in center.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together in a large container. Use 1/2 cup mixture to 1 cup hot water for 1 serving. Dry mixture placed in a pretty jar makes a great gift.

title: corn scallop
directions: Melt butter; add flour and dry seasonings.
Mix together.
Add scalded milk gradually and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add
corn,	egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: ruby chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with Accent and salt.
Brown in margarine in skillet (large).
Add onion, spices, orange juice and rind.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add walnuts and cranberries.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
(Be careful not to burn).
Stir occasionally as it simmers, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: anna lett's chicky buck buck
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook rice as directed (I use 5 minute kind).
Mix together with soup.
Heat and serve.

title: peanut butter and jelly squares
directions: Mix all together and put half in pan.
Spread 1 1/2 cups red raspberry jam over and put the rest of dough over.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, then add chopped nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° in a tube pan for 1 hour or in a Bundt pan for 50 minutes. While warm make a drizzle with cherry juice and confectioners sugar; drizzle over cake.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper and Italian herbs until well blended.
Divide into 4 portions and shape into flat, round cakes.

title: simple squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain.
Combine chopped onion, mayonnaise, 1 cup cheese, salt, pepper and oleo; mix well.
Pour in cooked squash and mix.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and brown.

title: see's fudge
directions: Boil butter, salt, milk, sugar, chocolate chips and vanilla for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Spread in buttered dish.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: sherbet party punch
directions: Put frozen juices in large bowl.
Stir in sherbet and soda. Add to keep cold.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Boil and drain lima beans.
Dice celery and pickles.
Slice onions.
In a bowl, mix pickles, onions, celery, sour cream, mayo, lemon juice and mustard.
Pour over lima beans; mix together. Refrigerate overnight, tightly covered.
Delicious!

title: cheese muffins
directions: Add sour cream to melted butter.
Stir in flour.
Mix in grated cheese.
Fill 4 tiny muffin pans sprayed well with Pam. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix oil and egg together.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: red pepper jam
directions: Really a relish of jam consistency.

title: delicious french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Beat eggs with cream and honey in large bowl.
Dip 4 slices of bread into mixture to coat thoroughly; transfer to plate.

title: polly's easy biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until flour is moistened. Drop by tablespoons on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot and simmer on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, onion mix and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: duck and wild rice
directions: Boil duck until done.
Mix rice with broth; mix to both cans of soup.
Mix well.
Place rice mix into casserole dish.
Place duck on top of rice.
(Be sure to remove duck from broth.)
Bake in oven (350°) until rice is done.
Enjoy!

title: holiday lizzies
directions: Chop fruits and nuts into medium size pieces.
Cream the butter.
Add sugar, creaming well.
Add beaten eggs; mix well. Stir in wine.
Dissolve soda in milk; stir into creamed mixture. Sift flour with spices.
Sift half of it over fruits.
Stir remaining flour into batter.
Mix fruits until flour-coated.
Add to batter, mixing well.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Shape with fingers.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 25 to 30 minutes, until slightly browned.
These keep well for a long time.
Yields 12 dozen.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix butter, zucchini, soda and sugar.
Add eggs and blend. Mix flour, salt and spices together and add to zucchini mixture. Add nuts and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Drain onion, pimentos, green pepper and chili sauce.
Do not use juice.
Add the ingredients to the cool egg, Mazola oil and vinegar mixture.
Makes 2 or 3 pint jars.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Add chopped onion and tomatoes.
Leave core in cabbage to hold together.
Wash and cut into small to medium wedges.
Lay wedges on beef and tomato mixture; cover and cook on low or simmer until cabbage reaches desired doneness.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Dip mushrooms in butter.
Stuff with mixture of sausage, bread crumbs, sauce and egg.
Top with a 1-inch square of sliced Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: zesty tuna salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Mix in other ingredients.
Use as sandwich spread or serve on English muffins.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, pecans and margarine.
Press into pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping. Blend well and spread on cool crust.
Chill.
Combine pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cheese layer.
Chill.
Repeat with vanilla pudding.
Frost with remaining whipped topping.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Next add remaining 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Bake at 375° 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: pineapple bundt cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box.
Add dry pudding mix. Bake in Bundt pan following directions on cake mix box
for Bundt cake baking times.

title: mocha chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, 1 cup Nestle Little Bits chocolate and butter; mix well.
Pat into 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and 2 1/2 inches up sides; set aside.

title: cream cheese mints(makes 100 mints.)
directions: *If weather is humid, add approximately 1 cup more of powdered sugar.

title: salmon delmonico
directions: Mix milk, flour, butter and salt and cook until done.
Add egg yolk and lemon juice.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot with 2 tablespoons shortening.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine with evaporated milk, milk, eggs, shredded cheeses, margarine, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased crock-pot.
Top with cheese slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, covered, on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix pudding, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend in Oreo cookies.
Chill.
Serve.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil Eagle Brand milk in cans in pot of water for 3 hours. Set out of water for about 15 minutes to cool.
Open cans of milk, put in bowl and cream with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Place in refrigerator to cool.
When cool, top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour yellow cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter on dry cake mix.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups very warm water.
Melt oleo.
Place in large bowl and cream with sugar.
Add egg.
Add water with dissolved yeast, then add flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonful in well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger.
Mix in taco seasoning according to package.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, cover bottom of pan with 3 tortillas.
Spread on meat mixture.
Cover with 3 tortillas.
Mix can of refried beans, 1/2 of sour cream and 1/2 cup of picante sauce.
Spread on bean mixture.
Cover with 3 tortillas. Mix 2 eggs, 1/2 of sour cream, 3/4 cup shredded cheese and 1/2 cup picante sauce.
Spread on cheese mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until cheese mixture is melted.
Place remainder of flour tortillas on oven rack and let dry.
Serve extra tortillas as chips.
You may also serve lasagna with your favorite toppings.

title: frosty ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease 3 quart casserole.
Butter and cut bread into squares. Make two layers of bread and cheese in casserole.
Mix together eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour milk/egg mixture over bread and cheese layers.
Cover and let stand overnight in fridge.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; to same water add onion, bayleaf and parsley.
Bring to boil and cook until tender.
Cook green pepper and garlic until soft.
Add to beans with other ingredients and cook until thickened.
Pour in dry sherry and serve with garnish sprinkled on top.
One cup equals 250 calories.

title: easy cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Surface of cake will be bumpy.)
Cool completely.

title: layered potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Leaving skins on, cut into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Peel onions and cut into 1/4-inch slices also. Separate into rings.
Starting with potatoes, layer potatoes, onion rings, salt, pepper and pats of butter in a large casserole, ending with onion rings.
Pour water in bottom of dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove from oven and cover with a layer of Velveeta.
Put in oven just long enough to melt.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in loaf or casserole dish.
Make a thick sauce of brown sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Spread on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.
Pour off grease.

title: sweet and sour sausages
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in ovenproof container.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring at 15-minute intervals. Serve in fondue pot over sterno or in crock-pot.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean and wash 6 large green peppers.
Mix well and fill each pepper shell.
Place in shallow baking dish; pour other 1/2 of mixture over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: Roll and dip in soda solution (water and soda).
Sprinkle salt on pretzels.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with mustard.

title: ray hance cake
directions: Put in mixing bowl the sugar and flour.
Combine and bring to a boil the water, margarine and cocoa.
Add to this mixture after it comes to a boil the eggs and vanilla.
Pour into sugar and flour mixture.
Stir well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Leave cake in pan and pour the following icing over warm cake.

title: sausage squares
directions: Break up sausage while browning in skillet; pour off most of the fat.
Add beaten eggs to cooled sausage; add milk, water and crumbs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook the eggplant in salted water for 30 minutes; drain.
Brown the onions in margarine until golden brown.
Add to beaten egg, eggplant and cornbread crumbs.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and bake until brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put a layer of broken bread pieces in bottom of large baking dish and sprinkle with half of sugar and oleo, which has been cut into pieces. Next, layer with marshmallows, coconut and raisins. Repeat bread, sugar and oleo layer. Beat eggs in 1/2 cup milk. Pour over mixture. Pour remaining 2 cups milk over all and press bread down to absorb the milk. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until light brown.

title: delicious dream cookies
directions: Gently combine.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10-12 minutes at 350°.
Delicious!

title: apple pie filling
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss apples with combined sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Turn into pastry.
Sprinkle with juice and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Slit top for steam.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Save 2 tablespoons of pan drippings and cook the onion in it until tender, not brown.
Add ham, undrained beans and water.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, garlic and bacon.
Simmer until done.
May have to add extra water.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Press crumbs on bottom of a lightly greased spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cook on wire rack.
Melt white chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, then cool.
Beat cream cheese at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add sugar.
Beat 5 minutes; add white chocolate.
Beat 5 minutes; add sour cream and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour over crust, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Run knife around sides of pan to release sides.
Let cool in pan on wire rack. Cover and chill 8 hours.
Remove pan and garnish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: christmas goulash
directions: Brown meat; add seasonings to taste.
Combine meat mixture and macaroni and cheese plus pork and beans and tomato sauce.
Mix all up.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cavatine
directions: Mix together in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a small bowl, beat together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
In a large bowl, beat the pudding and milk until it begins to thicken.
Fold in the Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
In a large plastic flowerpot, put a layer of crushed cookies, pudding mixture, cookies, etc., and end with cookie mixture on top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar together.
Add zucchini and all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together; add milk.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar; add to sweet potato mixture and pour into pie crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and margarine together.
Add beaten eggs, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients with hands. Take out 1/2 cup of the mixture and set it aside. To the rest add the remaining ingredients. After it is in the pan for baking, sprinkle the creamed crumbs on top. Bake in a moderate oven at 350°. (I add some salt.)

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil until tender. Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup vegetable sauce mixture with beef, bread crumbs, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Shape into a loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve remaining sauce, cold or heated, over meat loaf.

title: creamy apricot fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1/2 cup.
Combine jello and boiling water in blender.
Blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Add measured liquid, cream cheese and salad dressing.
Blend at high speed for 15 seconds.
Chill until slightly thickened; fold in fruit.
Chill until firm.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Break up spinach and set aside with strawberries.
Mix all other ingredients for dressing.
Slice strawberries in half, saving a few for garnish.
Just before meal is served, toss spinach and strawberries in dressing.

title: can't fail light bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add 4 cups of flour.
Stir and then beat until smooth. Stir in 2 cups flour and beat again.
Add remaining 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour and stir.
This will be a soft dough.
Cover tightly and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and shape into rolls or loaves of bread.
Bake at 425° for rolls or at 400° for loaves.

title: jello kanten
directions: Dissolve 1
cup tap water with unflavored gelatin.
Mix together Jell-O,
sugar
and boiling water.
Add Knox gelatine mixture; mix well.	Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chile dip
directions: In small bowl, mash garlic and salt to a paste.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Chop tomatoes.
Slice bacon crosswise.
Brown in large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic paste and onions; cook until onions are golden.
Add chopped tomatoes, reserved liquid, chilies and sugar.
Stir over medium-low heat 15 minutes.
Add hot pepper sauce to taste.
Turn into a heated 1-quart casserole dish and top with cheese.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: golden butterscotch fudge
directions: Drizzle rum extract over raisins; cover and let stand several hours or overnight.
Cook together sugars, margarine and milk until soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and stir in chips and Marshmallow Creme until melted and blended.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Cut bread crumbs into small pieces.
Brown in oven at 350 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes.
Watch carefully!
Heat margarine and sprinkle with seasonings.
Pour margarine/seasoning mixture over browned bread crumbs.
Put back in oven for 5 - 10 minutes to dry out.
Store in air-tight container.

title: peanut streusel pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar until mealy.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the mixture over baked pie shell.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in top of a double boiler.
Stir in scalded milk.
Cook until thick.
Stir small amount of cooked filling into egg yolks, then combine the rest of the filling and yolks together and cook several minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.
Pimento may be added for color.

title: goddess cashew chicken salad
directions: In large bowl combine chicken, celery, green pepper, onion, pimento and salt; toss lightly.
In small bowl, gently fold dressing into whipped cream. Combine chicken-vegetable mixture and dressing, tossing lightly.
Chill.
Just before serving, add cashews.

title: steak and dumplings
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Cut off fat.
Brown meat on both sides; drain off all grease.
Add water and seasoning. Cook 1 hour or more.
Check water; if low, add more water.
Meat should be covered.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks, being careful not to tear the whites. Place the whites on a serving dish and set aside.

title: "hopping john" peas
directions: Soak peas in cold water for 1 hour. Drain and cover again with water and add ham, onion, salt and pepper. Cook covered about 1 hour on medium heat. Cook rice separately and add to peas. Cook a few minutes longer. Serve with tomato gravy.

title: noodles and sauerkraut
directions: Cook noodles with chicken.
When done, put noodles and sauerkraut in frypan.
Fry until brown.
Serve and eat.

title: simple salmon casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni in 6 cups boiling, salted water for 12 minutes.
Drain, but do not rinse.
While cooking macaroni, combine mushroom soup, evaporated milk and pimento.
Add liquid from salmon, the salmon flaked in large chunks and bones removed and half of grated cheese.
Mix well and stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn mixture into an oiled 6 cup baking dish.

title: crab supper pie
directions: Sprinkle cheese evenly over bottom of pastry shell.
Top with crab meat; sprinkle with green onion.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel, mustard and mace.
Pour over crab meat.
Top with almonds.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes until set. Remove and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: german potato dumplings
directions: Cook potatoes in skins in boiling water until tender. Dry over pan.
Peel and rice.
Cool.
In bowl combine and blend the potatoes, flour,eggs and salt.
Shape into balls, lower into salted, simmering water.
Cook 10-12 minutes.
Remove and drain.

title: cashew chicken(a springfield, mo trademark)
directions: Flour chicken and let set 15 minutes.
Beat eggs with milk. Add salt and pepper.
Add chicken.
Let set 10 minutes.
Remove and roll in flour again.
Deep fry in hot peanut oil.

title: sour cream-chocolate bit cake
directions: Mix butter with the 1 cup sugar until blended, then beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir flour with baking powder, soda and cinnamon, then blend with creamed mixture.
Mix in the sour cream. Pour batter into a greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter the chocolate bits evenly over the batter, then sprinkle with the remaining tablespoon of sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until cake just begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: richmond goulash (1930)
directions: Stir minced onion in an iron frying pan with meat.
As it cooks, pour off any fat.
Add soup and water.
Cook until done (about 5 minutes).
Pour over toast or an English muffin.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine soup, taco mix and hot pepper sauce.
Stir until blended.
Spread mixture on a large serving plate 6 inches around. Spread sides and top of bean mixture with sour cream to cover. Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time (at least 4 hours).
Before serving, surround with tortilla chips.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix and stir ingredients thoroughly.

title: oven meal
directions: Place ingredients in a baking dish in order as listed; sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake until bubbly and hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare the elbow macaroni; drain and place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Next, using a double boiler, melt the margarine. When it is melted, stir in approximately 1/4 cup of flour. Mix thoroughly. When margarine and flour are mixed, slowly begin to blend in milk, stirring constantly. Stir until you have a smooth white sauce mixture, then add the cheese chunks a few at a time until all the cheese is fully melted and a smooth cheese sauce is created. Pour the cheese sauce over the prepared macaroni. Fold gently until well mixed. Sprinkle the cornflake crumbs over the top. Bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Mix together.
Cut cake into 2 layers.
Frost and sprinkle with coconut.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce. Mix well. Stir in cold water; mix well.
Chill until partially set. Fold in pineapple with liquid and oranges. Coat a 9 x 13 with nonstick cooking spray. Chill until firm about 4 hours.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cheese and tomatoes; stir until cheese is melted.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: scrumptious apple coffee cake
directions: Grease a
x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with a fork.
Gently fold in next 3 ingredients, 1/4 cup
of the
corn
syrup,
and
the cinnamon and nutmeg until blended. Spread
evenly
in
pan.
Mix
remaining corn syrup, walnut pieces and margarine.
Spoon evenly over batter.
Bake in a
350° oven for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, baking powder and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs, oil and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy. Add dry ingredients, sugar and pineapple alternately.
Stir until dry ingredients are mixed.
Stir in zucchini until moist.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured loaf pans; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts at 425° about 45 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tasty chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, French dressing and soup mix in blender. Pour over chicken pieces in casserole dish.
Marinate for 1 hour. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender, basting frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach; squeeze out most of the water.
Saute onion in butter; add to the spinach with the cream cheese until melted. Add cooked rice if desired.

title: beef fried rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package. Spray a skillet with cooking spray and heat until hot. Beat egg and pour in hot skillet. Cook 1 minute or until firm. Remove and cut into strips. In same skillet, cook ground beef, mushrooms and celery over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes. In small bowl, combine soy sauce, sesame oil and hot pepper sauce; mix well. Stir soy sauce mixture into ground beef mixture. Add pea pods, onions, cooked eggs and cooked rice. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: baby drumsticks
directions: Use the part of the chicken wing that looks like a drumstick. Put salt and pepper to taste, dash of soul food seasoning salt in pancake batter.
Dip each drumstick in the batter and fry in hot oil until tender.

title: home-style macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni to package directions; drain.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat stirring until smooth and bubbly (1 minute). Stir in milk, cream cheese, salt, pepper and mustard.
Continue cooking until sauce is thickened, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: *Use all cans the same size.

title: oriental salad
directions: Break up spinach a little bit.
Toss salad ingredients with spinach.

title: jicama salad with citrus dressing
directions: Cut jicama into thick julienne strips.
Combine jicama and red onion in serving bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered jar.
Shake to mix.
Pour dressing over jicama and toss.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kraut balls
directions: Cook crumbled sausage and onions until brown.
Remove from heat and drain grease.
Squeeze kraut between paper towels and snip kraut into 1-inch pieces.

title: pineapple mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons of juice.
Melt marshmallows in double boiler.
Add 3 tablespoons pineapple juice to mixture.
Add softened cream cheese and pineapple.
Pour into mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mold can be made 2 or 3 days ahead.

title: green olive spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute first six ingredients until beef and pork are done. Drain grease!
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer for 1 hour.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
In 1-quart
saucepan, over medium heat, cook onion until tender. Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes; cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ginger peach dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in peaches.
Spoon into individual molds, serving bowl or individual dessert dishes.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Mix it all together (except Cheddar cheese).
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of it. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: pork tenderloin and mushrooms
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and brown sugar.
Heat oil in frying pan until very hot.
Stir and fry the meat until lightly browned on all sides(3 to 5 minutes).
Add the soy mixture and stir until blended.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add the mushrooms; turn heat to high and stir-fry and cook until mushrooms are tender (about 5 minutes).
Liquid will be almost all absorbed.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and salt the ground beef. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer a few minutes before serving.
You may add chopped onion to browning hamburger meat.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and corned beef together.
Mix the other ingredients and pour over meat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Cut each breast in half again.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice, white pepper and garlic.
Add chicken.
Marinate overnight, turning occasionally.
Roll in crushed crackers.
Put on cookie sheet and brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients. Place in loaf pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Blend sugar, milk and butter in saucepan and cook on low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and cornstarch.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Combine sugar, juice and rind.
Add milk and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Don't worry if it looks curdled.
Pour into freezing tray or glass baking dish. Freeze firm.
Transfer chunks to chilled bowl and beat with electric beater until light.
Pile quickly back into tray and refreeze.
Holds up well.

title: slow cooker cheese dip
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and sausage over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Add cheese and tomatoes. Mix well. Cover and cook on low heat for 4 hours or until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: coconut custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Makes two pies.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Must be solid in middle.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, pecans, mayonnaise, onion, black pepper and cayenne pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into ring. Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator for 1 day or longer.
May fill center with jelly.
Serve with thin wheat crackers.
Yield: 70 servings.

title: rhubarb-cherry jam
directions: Combine rhubarb with sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, cook until rhubarb is tender, about 30 minutes on slow heat.
Stir in cherry pie filling and cherry gelatin.
Cook to boil.
Cool completely and pack into containers.
Put in refrigerator or freezer.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese together. Stiff raw manicotti with this mixture.
Fill bottom of pan with sauce which consists of the spaghetti sauce, Italian seasoning and basil.
Line pan with noodles and cover with sauce. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all together in large casserole dish and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Salt chicken pieces and lay on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 1 more hour.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat the white sugar, oil and eggs until lemon colored.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Blend orange juice, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Melt butter in boiling water.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to orange juice mixture.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: date balls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Add dates, coconut and nuts.
Pour into 2-quart casserole greased with margarine or butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, stir real good.
When cool, drop by teaspoons and roll in granulated sugar.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together well.
Uses heaping teaspoonful mix for serving. Serve hot or cold.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: summer grilled chicken salad
directions: Poke holes in chicken and marinate with dressing for 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Then cook on grill until done.
Cool.

title: garbage dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. This is great with corn chips, also on hamburgers.

title: bean and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook beans and broccoli per directions.
Combine with next 4 ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with Rice Krispies.
Spread on top of B/B casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dump pie(hunting man's favorite)
directions: Mix together in bowl the flour, sugar and milk.
Then add your fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until the crust comes to the top and browns.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix wet and dry ingredients separately.
Combine the two well. Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Boil cleaned and sliced zucchini until tender.
In a bowl mix eggs, onion, green pepper, mayo and Parmesan cheese.
Fold in cooked, drained zucchini into bowl mixture.
Pour into a sprayed or buttered pan or casserole dish.
Dot with margarine and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until shortening is the size of peas.
Add buttermilk, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness; cut with a round cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: cherry delight
directions: Grease baking dish; pour in cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Pour melted butter evenly over cherries and cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Add nuts if you want.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Add 1 cup warm water, yeast mixture, salt and oil.	Add 4 cups flour; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll out each in shape of pie.
Use plenty of flour.
Cut into pie shape wedges and roll each from large end.
(Eight sections to each pie shape.)
Let stand and rise.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 crescents.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Put in casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each tortilla into 8 wedges.
Place on baking sheet and bake about 10 minutes or until crisp.
Remove from oven.
In large skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is browned, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans; heat until hot, about 2 minutes.
Place lettuce on large serving platter.
Spoon chili over lettuce.
Top with yogurt and sprinkle with cheese.
Surround platter with tortilla chips.

title: menorah sandwich
directions: Spread cream cheese on bread.
Arrange pretzel stick "candles" and carrot stick "shamash" to make a Chanukah menorah.
Use raisins to "light" your menorah.
Serves 1.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together 3 times the flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in medium size saucepan (medium heat).
Remove; stir in sugar, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla, then mix in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy hawaiian cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: luscious orange pie
directions: Spread over cooled crust.
Top with 8 ounces frozen whipped topping.
Sprinkle over additional 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in small saucepan. Add water, vanilla and butter. Cook over low heat until thick.

title: corn and green chile casserole
directions: Cook corn; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; add cream cheese and stir until well blended.
Stir in corn, sugar and green chiles.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Good easy recipe!

title: best carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Mix all ingredients well.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: pasta shells florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg white, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg until blended.
Fill each shell with a heaping tablespoon of spinach mixture.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon sauce over shells; cover with foil.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until thoroughly combined.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers, etc.

title: baked chicken in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream with seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces into sour cream mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter into baking pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Works great with boneless skinless chicken breast, lite sour cream.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Serve with wheat crackers or raw vegetables.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes. Cook until a fork pierces them.
Mix Good Seasons Italian dressing according to the directions on the package.
Marinate the cooked potatoes in the Good Seasons Italian dressing and onion for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: george jr.'s refrigerator muffins
directions: Combine bran and Bran Buds.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand while mixing remaining ingredients.
Cream together egg, shortening and sugar.
To first mixture, add 1/2 quart buttermilk, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add all and stir until combined. Add raisins, if desired.
Refrigerate batter.
Do not freeze. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in greased muffin tins.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: hershey chocolate nut cake
directions: Sift flour; cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy, adding eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Melt Hershey bar on low heat (this will be rather thick).
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk which has soda dissolved in it and flavorings; blend well.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured stem pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(It may take a little longer; test after this length of time.)

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Grease a pie plate with margarine.
Put a layer of sliced jalapeno peppers to cover bottom of pie plate.
(Add more if you like it extra spicy.)
Sprinkle 1 lb. grated cheddar cheese over peppers.
Beat 6 eggs and pour over cheese.
Bake at 300 - 325 for one hour.
Let cool before cutting.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown meat.
Drain; add rest of ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Serve hot with Doritos, Tostitos or taco chips.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except whole wheat flour.
Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add beaten egg and sour milk, alternately with dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: fancy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Saute onions and bell peppers in bacon drippings.
Mix all and bake in a casserole dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: peter's ice cream cake
directions: You will also need whatever decoration for the top that you want to use. Keep in mind you have to work quickly, so it's best to keep things simple and easy.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Cream together 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1 cup oil.
Add beaten eggs, 1 cup orange juice and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder and add gradually to egg mixture.
Peel and slice thin apples.
Mix together cinnamon and sugar.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Start with layer of batter and alternate with batter on top.
Bake at 320° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: jello cranberry salad
directions: Grind all fruit. Add sugar and mix well. Dissolve jello in water and chill until it begins to set.
Mix fruit and jello. Chill to serve.

title: 14-carat cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Mixture will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 3 layers.

title: mamma norden's yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar and salt with flour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix Crisco and flour with mixer, then add water with yeast that is dissolved.
Let rise 3 hours, then knead down.
Roll out.
Place in pan.
Rise a short time.
Grease tops.
Bake at 350° to 400° until golden brown.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 8)
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch dish. Sprinkle 1 package grated sharp Cheddar cheese and cover with crushed potato chips (about 1 1/2 cups).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions except add coconut and flavoring.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Combine the two.
Whip milk until holds peak and fold in mixture.
Cover bottom of large pan with crumbs and pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill several hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Form into a log.
Chill and cut into slices.
You can also roll into balls and chill.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: e-z pie crust
directions: Mix first three ingredients right in an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Mix oil and milk together in a bowl and then add to flour mixture.

title: mexican chicken rice skillet
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine mayonnaise, broth, rice, chilies, chili powder and cumin.
Mix well.
Top with chicken.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Mix together crackers, milk and eggs in bowl.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into greased 3-cup casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: easy borsch
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water to boil; stir in soup mix, beets, sugar and lemon juice.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until beets are tender.
Remove beets and cool slightly.
Grate beets coarsely; return to saucepan.
Serve hot topped with sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Mix 1 can water with soup.
Place 1 cup in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chicken in dish.
Sprinkle with small can of mushrooms.
Add cooking wine to remaining soup; mix well and pour over chicken.
Cover; bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove cover last 1/2 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding together, blending until thick.
Fold in sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip container.
Alternate in a 9 x 13-inch pan the wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: yeast rolls
directions: "Mix egg, milk, cheese.
Stir around real quick till it turns yellow, brown, pink, purple and blue.
Put in oven and let it melt. Then take it out and eat it."

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: mom's squirrel pie
directions: Cut squirrel up and parboil in baking soda.
When it foams, take off heat and drain.
Rinse good.
Put back in pot with diced onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until done.
Bone it.
Save broth.
Cook diced potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in broth. Add deboned squirrel and boil well.
Have biscuit crust ready. Add a few celery seed to crust.
Pour stew into a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with crust immediately.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Put spaghetti in large baking dish. Cut up chicken. Cook peppers and onions with mushroom soup until tender. Put chicken on top of spaghetti. Put peppers and onion mix on top of chicken. Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Slice onions and dice green pepper.
Combine vegetables and salt.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables.
Heat thoroughly, but don't boil!
Pack immediately into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onion.
Then mix with the Veg-All, chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Crush the Ritz crackers and mix with one stick melted margarine.
Place the Veg-All mixture in a casserole dish and cover with the Ritz crackers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken rice dish(or tuna)
directions: Combine salt, mustard, eggs and 2 cups milk.
Pour over rice and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (until knife comes out clean).
Melt butter and add flour.
Combine with 3 cups milk and cook and stir until thick.
Add mushroom soup and chicken or tuna.
Heat until warm.
Cut rice dish into squares.
Serve with sauce spooned over the top.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cook on low in crock-pot approximately 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: sliced z's
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add zucchini and Italian tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on medium-low until zucchini is tender.
Serve with freshly grated Parmesan or Mozzarella cheese.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies according to package directions; cool.
Punch holes in brownies with a fork and pour coffee mixture over it. Set aside.
Make mousse according to directions.
Break Heath bars into small pieces.
Crumble 1/2 of the brownie mixture and place in the bottom of a glass dish.
Layer with 1/2 the mousse, 1/2 the candy and 1/2 the whipped topping.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut.
Use teaspoon to drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: anise kringle
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
With hands, roll small pieces of dough to pencil thickness.
Cut into 8 to 9-inch lengths.
Form into pretzel shapes and arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Strain and serve.
You can put spices in basket of percolator and avoid straining.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Fry chicken.
Put in casserole.
Boil other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pancakes(here's an easy pancake recipe.)
directions: Beat well all ingredients in a bowl.
Dip 1/4 cup on grill for each pancake.
Add butter and syrup for flavor.

title: oriental turkey
directions: Place turkey in a container or dish for marinating.
Combine the sherry, honey, soy sauce, salt and cinnamon and pour over the turkey.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain the turkey and place in a foil-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke oyster soup or artichoke crabmeat soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter and brown lightly.
Add flour until mixed with butter.
Add broth slowly.
Stir until smooth. Chop artichoke hearts into small pieces and add to mixture.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for about 1 hour, covered. Chop oysters and add to ingredients.
Cook slowly another 30 minutes.
Heat milk (or half and half for richer taste) to soup before serving.

title: karen's crab meat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise and onion together.
Spread in small pie plate or dish.
Add sauce to top. Shred crab meat and sprinkle over sauce.
Sprinkle parsley over crab meat.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: a.m.e. punch
directions: Add ingredients to a gallon pitcher and enough water to fill.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into 8 to 10 balls.
Partially roll out on floured board.
Put in round cake pans and flatten out with hand to cover bottom of pan.
Bake until brown.
Turn out on cake rack and completely cool.
Stack, putting cooked, dried apples on as you stack.

title: royal anne cherry pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, cherries, flour, water and soda, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 9 pieces.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.

title: fix and forget pork chops and rice
directions: In saucepan, combine uncooked rice, water, undrained corn, carrot, onion and thyme.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in soup.
Put in a baking dish.
Trim fat from pork chops; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange on rice mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir together bread crumbs and paprika. Add margarine; toss gently to mix.
Remove foil from chops.
Put paprika mix atop of chops.
Bake, uncovered, about 15 minutes more or until rice is tender and pork is slightly pink just near the bone.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: microwave perfect fudge
directions: Cook for 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir and cook for another 2 to 3 minutes until melted well.
Stir and let stand, then cut into squares.

title: california chili
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add canned goods and spice to taste. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.

title: veggie bars
directions: Cover bottom of pan, 15 x 10-inch, with rolled out rolls. Bake at 350° until light brown (7 to 8 minutes).
Beat cream cheese with mayo and Hidden Valley Ranch until smooth.
Mix veggies and sprinkle cheese on last.
Fridge and cut into bars.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Whip heavy cream until just about to separate.
Place in refrigerator.
