Beat egg whites until they peak.
Add powdered sugar and beat until stiff peaks.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate over boiling water.
Combine whipped cream and egg whites; fold together. Dribble chocolate over and blend.
Spoon into serving dishes and refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saut onion in margarine; prepare rice and broccoli.
Drain broccoli. Add cheese, soup and milk to onion mixture; heat thoroughly.
Grease 8 x 10-inch dish with margarine. Layer broccoli, rice and cheese mixture.
Repeat layer. Sprinkle with paprika before putting in oven. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Boil 3 minutes.
Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Spray foil with Pam.
Line crackers on foil.
Pour sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, until crackers begin to float.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Spread when melted.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cut in squares on lines as soon as mixture hardens.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix soda with water; pour over dates.
Let cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Add nuts, date mixture and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together the chocolate chips, nuts and eggs.
Add the sugars, butter and flour. Add vanilla.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake for 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a large heavy skillet with heat-proof handle on grid over medium coals.
Add zucchini, squash, mushrooms, bell pepper, cumin, salt and black pepper.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato and green onion.
Continue to cook and stir for 1 minute.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Fry meat; drain and set aside.
Melt cheese in double boiler and mix all ingredients with cheese.
Spread on two loaves party rye bread.
Can be frozen.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes if frozen or 5 minutes if thawed.

title: tuna cheese chowder
directions: In 3-quart pan, cook carrots and onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add milk, broth and flour.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in tuna, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Heat through.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: old fashioned pull candy
directions: Combine butter, water, vinegar and sugar in large saucepan. Cook until a hard ball forms when dropped into cool water. Do not stir while cooking or it will go to sugar. Remove from heat and add flavoring. Pour into greased pan to cool, but don't allow to harden. Grease hands and put small amount of flour on them and pull the candy as long as you can. When candy becomes too hard to pull, cut into small pieces with scissors.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken in small chunks.
Cook vegetables until tender. Mix ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Using biscuit recipe on back of Bisquick, roll and cut out biscuits. Place on top of chicken and vegetable mixture, side by side.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: tasty salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add Miracle Whip until desired consistency.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix first five ingredients and fold in berries.
Pour in muffin pan and bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 12 to 15 muffins.

title: peanut butter drizzle
directions: Combine and mix well.

title: pizza hot dish(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart glass casserole.
Add onion and garlic.
Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is set, stirring once.
Drain.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Place green beans in a large pot of water.
Bring water to a full boil and turn off heat.
Once boiling stops, rinse beans with cold water to stop cooking.
Cut bacon into small pieces and cook in saute pan.
After a couple of minutes, add onion.
When bacon is almost done, add green beans, then tomatoes.
Stir to coat evenly. Salt and pepper to taste and serve.

title: creamed ham and asparagus
directions: In a saucepan, cook asparagus in a small amount of water until tender; drain and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons milk.
Add butter, salt, pepper and remaining milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Add parsley, ham, eggs, cheese and asparagus; cook and stir over low heat until ham is warmed and cheese melted.
Serve over toast or biscuits.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: scotch scones
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add enough buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Divide into 3 portions and roll each into a circle on a floured surface.
Cut into 4 wedges.
Bake on griddle or electric skillet preheated to 350°.
Bake on each side until golden brown.

title: baked chicken breast cornbread stuffing
directions: In large frypan, place all but 1 tablespoon of the butter and melt over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add collard greens and cook until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and place onion and collards in large bowl.
Add cornbread, egg and sage.
Mix well and cool.
Between two sheets of plastic wrap, place chicken breasts, smooth side down.
Pound gently with meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened.
Place 1/8 of stuffing on center of each breast; roll and tuck ends under.
On large greased baking pan with sides, place chicken.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon of butter and brush lightly on chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
(At this point, chicken may be covered and placed in refrigerator for up to 24 hours.)
Place in 375° oven and cook about 20 minutes or until meat is no longer pink when tested with a knife.
Slice each breast into 5 slices and arrange on plate with Sweet Onion Gravy and rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and add flour to bacon drippings and mix well.
Place mixture and bacon pieces in slow cooker.
Add all other ingredients; stir together thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low heat 7 to 9 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: world famous meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, onion, green pepper, couple of shakes of Worcestershire sauce and oatmeal thoroughly.
Place in pan or baking dish.
Pat together and round off so hamburger is not touching the sides.

title: quivering jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
In a small bowl, stir together corn meal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, buttermilk, sour cream and creamed corn.
Stir in melted butter and diced peppers.
(Use hot jalapenos for very hot bread; use mild chiles otherwise.)
Blend dry ingredients into wet ingredients.
Pour into prepared skillet.
Top with grated cheese. Bake until top is dark, golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 4-quart casserole.
Crush 1 cup cracker crumbs or potato chips and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: In covered blender container, blend all ingredients at high speed just until finely chopped.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes about 3 cups.
Good with fresh vegetables.

title: cocktail wienies
directions: Heat the mustard, jelly and horseradish together slowly.
Add wieners.
Serve hot.
Can keep in crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: oatmeal freezer cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix margarine and sugar and add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Stir in flour mixture. Add rolled oats and raisins.
Divide dough into four parts.
Shape each part into a roll about 6 inches long and 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans. Shape into ball. Chill slightly; roll in pecans.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in water until tender.
Place broccoli in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice water chestnuts and place over broccoli.
Cook chicken at 400° for 1 hour.
Cool and dice; put over broccoli.
Blend remaining ingredients for sauce.
Pour over casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for half hour.
Cover with cheese and cook another 15 minutes.

title: four seasons salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and cool pasta. Combine French dressing with sour cream, mixing well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix meat and eggs (plus bacon) to pasta and mix well.
Pour dressing over mixture and stir as needed to cover with dressing.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: empire biscuits
directions: Cream butter and add sugar, creaming well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch rounds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes, or until very lightly brown at edges.
Let cool thoroughly.
Spread half the cookies with jam; top with remaining cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Place broccoli in large bowl, add onion and raisins.
Toss well.

title: pecan drops
directions: Mix together with big spoon or grease hands with butter and mix with hands.
Roll in small balls and chill.
Melt 12 ounce package chocolate morsels with a 4 ounce package paraffin in double boiler.
Put toothpicks in each ball and dip into chocolate mixture.
After dipping, put on wax paper.

title: orange balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in remaining powdered sugar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel cooked potatoes and cut in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Slice butter evenly over potatoes. Spread sugar over this, and drizzle syrup over potatoes without ever stirring.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top, and bake around 30 minutes or until glazed and heated through.

title: sweet peppers
directions: Make thin syrup of above and add cleaned pepper strips.
Cook about 5 minutes and put in sterilized jars.
Can use red and green peppers for color.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: delicious nine day slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, green pepper, and onion.
Combine sugar, corn oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Bring mixture to a boil for 5 minutes.

title: molasses cookies(crisp and chewy)
directions: Melt butter and let cool to room temperature. In a large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and egg; beat well. In a small bowl, combine water and soda and add to creamed mixture. Stir in molasses and flour; blend well. Drop dough by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Space about 3-inches apart. Bake in 350° oven for 7 to 9 minutes. Let cool completely before storing.

title: settlens beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion; drain.
Put in crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Blend and put over Jell-O mix.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: real corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Melt in bread pan the lard.
Pour sizzling grease into the mixture.
Pour into a hot pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: agression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and mix by hand until completely blended.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut. Flatten on cookie sheet with greased bottom of a drinking glass. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soups, vegetables and chicken broth.
Pour into large casserole dish or several small ones.
Top with broken pie crusts.
Pour butter over crusts and bake for 55 minutes at 300° to 325° until brown.

title: billionaires
directions: Grease a sheet of wax paper.
Melt caramels, evaporated milk and vanilla in top of a double boiler or microwave.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool until firm. Melt Hershey bar and paraffin in top of a double boiler or microwave.
Dip caramel pieces into chocolate mixture to coat. Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add the remaining. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in walnut pieces. Bake 30 minutes at 300°. Cool for 10 minutes, then roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken florentine
directions: In a skillet, over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in butter (about 5 minutes).
Stir in chicken.
Saute for 15 minutes. Add cornstarch, broth, basil and spinach.
Bring to a boil and then simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: mom's corny cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased baking pan. Bake at 450° until done.

title: tangy broccoli and potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender. Drain, set aside and keep warm.
Cut broccoli spears into 1/4 inch slices.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain, set aside and keep warm.
Combine parsley and next 5 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in green onions and hot sauce. Place potatoes and broccoli in a serving bowl.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over vegetables and toss lightly.
Sprinkle pimiento over vegetables.
Top with egg slices. Serve warm.

title: coconut twists
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and milk.
Mix flour mixture in.
Add vanilla. Mix together well.
Make 3 balls, roll out thin.
Spread melted butter over dough.
Sprinkle sugar and coconut over half of dough.
Fold in half, cut into strips about 1/2 inch wide and twist.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, saute green peppers and onions in olive oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Place the chicken breasts over the vegetables.
In a bowl, combine tomato sauce, chilies and seasons.
Pour over the chicken, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream cream cheese and sugar, add in cool whip and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour in pie crust and top with pie filling. Chill and serve.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In pan melt oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil. In bowl put sugar, flour and salt.
Pour melted ingredients over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Put in 12 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven in slightly greased pan.
Spread to sides and corners.

title: chocolate oatmeal crisp
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add sugar, milk and cocoa. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Blend in peanut butter and vanilla. Add salt and oatmeal mixing well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Let cool.

title: summer squash with dill and sour cream
directions: Peel squash and take out seeds.
Cut into skinny "French fries" shape.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes in water slightly salted with a tablespoon of vinegar.
Saute onion in shortening.
Stir in flour to thicken. Add
water to onion and flour mixture. Cook and thicken sauce.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons vinegar and sugar to the sauce.
Add dill weed and mix in the drained squash.
Put in sour cream just before serving.

title: sicilian chicken
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook slightly tender about 10 minutes.
Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
Add to onion mixture. Cook, turning chicken frequently, until pinkness is gone.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until heated through.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sugar tortillas
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening thoroughly. Add water slowly until dough is formed.
Cover and let rest for 15 minutes.
Divide into balls and roll into thin rounds.
Cook on hot griddle until done on both sides.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar in medium bowl. Beat eggs well and add to flour mixture.

title: chicken-noodle soup
directions: Heat all ingredients, except for noodles, to boiling in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done (about 45 minutes).
Cook noodles as directed on package. Remove chicken from broth and let cool slightly.
Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Add chicken pieces and noodles to broth. Heat about 5 minutes.

title: rosie's pecan pralines
directions: Pour milk into sugar to make a soft mix.
Add butter and cook until this boils, stirring continuously.
Add pecans and cook until thick (soft ball stage).
Take off of the fire.
Add vanilla and beat approximately 5 minutes or until it loses its gloss. Pour on buttered pan or waxed paper.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Mix flour and salt together.
Add soda, cinnamon, cloves and ginger to flour mixture.
Add to shortening mixture.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: golden fruit salad dressing
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler; add fruit juices, sugar and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook mixture over gently boiling water until thick (about 10 minutes), stirring constantly; cool. Just before using, fold in the whipped cream.
Yields about 3/4 pint dressing.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix ground beef, rice and 1 egg; make into small balls.
Put into large pan and add 2 cups tomato juice and 1 cup water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Continue cooking until done.
May be cooked in a crock-pot.
It thickens as it cooks.
Serve with hot French bread and a salad.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and bake. When cake is done and while hot, punch holes in cake. Pour coconut on cake, then condensed milk. Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: mediterranean chicken stew
directions: Soften onion in oil. Stir in garlic, mushrooms, roughly chopped tomatoes, olives, stock, juice, chutney, rosemary and bring to a boil. Simmer a few minutes. Add chicken and simmer again until chicken is thoroughly heated. Add more stock, if necessary. Serve with pasta, rice or couscous.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, butter well (about 1/4 cup melted). Cover bottom of pan with bread slices, then cover bread with slices of American cheese, then ham.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and pepper.
Beat vigorously and pour over dry ingredients.
Top with Cheddar cheese and croutons.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lou's chess pie
directions: Melt oleo or butter.
Add sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil. Set
aside	to cool.
Beat eggs, vanilla and salt until lemon colored.
Stir
into
sugar mixture slowly, making sure the eggs do	not
cook
or
pie will be lumpy.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Lightly grease pan.
Cut Crisco into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Slowly add milk, just enough until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead gently 2 to 3 times on lightly floured surface.
Pinch off some; roll into a ball and place on baking pan and mash it down a little.
Put a little Crisco on top of biscuit, then bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow rolls
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 1 cup peanut butter over warm burner.
Add nuts, Cracker Jacks and marshmallow topping.
Roll into round balls and dip into powdered sugar.

title: quick cream of spinach soup
directions: Mix milk into soups in a saucepan until smooth and creamy. Add spinach (drained).
Increase recipe proportionately for more servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugars and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan over a medium heat, bringing to a low boil. Stir constantly and continue low boil until mixture reaches soft boil stage.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add 2 eggs and 1 cup of flour at a time, beating after each addition. Beat in extracts. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour, until done.

title: vanilla layer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk; beat well for about 10 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch pans for about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Raisins and nuts (or both) may be added.
Frost with mocha icing.

title: ham and cheese quiche even a man will love!!
directions: Beat eggs, mayonnaise and milk until fluffy.
Fold in additional ingredients.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until done and lightly brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add next 5 ingredients, mix well.
Add next 2 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields three 9-inch pans.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan and preheat oven to 350°. Combine cake mix, 1 can pie filling, oil and eggs; beat well with mixer until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool in pan 25 minutes; invert onto rack to finish cooling.
When cool, cut in half to make two layers.
Using half a can of pie filling, cover first layer, then cover with half the Cool Whip. Repeat with top layer.
Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: dump salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.
Put fresh berries on top, if desired, when ready to serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Bake in iron skillet at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown onions; add meat and other ingredients.
Add Worcestershire sauce last and cook all together for 1 hour.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Bring to a full boil sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until fully blended. Add oatmeal (1 cup coconut may be substituted for 1 cup oatmeal). Place by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate once they have set up.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Pour drippings from a roast beef into baking pan.
Place in a 400° oven until drippings bubble.
Mix eggs and milk, then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into hot drippings for 45 minutes.
Serve with roast.
Serves 6.

title: black forest brownies
directions: Grease and flour 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking pan.
Set aside. Combine cake mix, pie filling, eggs and vanilla extract in a large bowl.
Stir, using a wooden spoon, until all ingredients are well mixed.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: practically "foolproof" meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add marshmallow cream.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie filling, sealing edge of crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
Drain and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Add shredded cheese, soup, pimento, onion and pepper to macaroni. Stir well. Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Pour melted butter on top of crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice 3/8-inch thick.
Separate into rings. Pour buttermilk or ice water into shallow pan; add onion rings and allow to soak 30 minutes.

title: cabbage pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes. Arrange in casserole dish, (salt) with cabbage.
Put pork chops on top.
Mix soup with milk and flour and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden meatballs
directions: Whisk golden mushroom soup and sour cream in a medium bowl. If mixture is too thick, add a little milk. Bake meatballs for 45 minutes before adding mixture. Put meatballs in a crock-pot. Mix mixture throughout meatballs. Leave on high for 1 hour. Then put to low just before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; save liquid.
Heat milk and add rice; let stand 5 minutes.
Add salmon liquid and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, green peppers, onions, lemon juice and salmon.
Mix well. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until firm in center.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes. Loosen from sides with spatula and invert on serving platter.

title: almond-stuffed bacon-wrapped dates
directions: Soak round toothpicks in hot water several minutes. Drain. Cut bacon slices in thirds (or half is okay). Stuff date with whole almond, wrap with bacon and secure with toothpick. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Drain; serve warm. Yields about 75 pieces. Freeze baked or unbaked; if unbaked, bake straight from freezer at 400° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in the teriyaki marinade for several hours.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Pour Russian dressing into a large skillet and bring to a boil.
Add chicken and cook on medium heat for 25 minutes, until chicken becomes glazed.
Stir over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Simmer chicken 40 to 50 minutes, until tender.
Remove from bones and dice.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: pretzel snack
directions: Break up pretzels in a plastic container with lid.
Add dry dressing packet and shake well.
Add oil and shake well again. Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 350°, stirring occasionally. Bake 7 minutes for regular pretzels.
Bake 10 minutes for hard pretzels.

title: cream of coconut pound cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, break into small pieces and put in greased 9x13 inch baking dish. Dilute soup with milk and pour over chicken. Mix dressing with hot water and butter and crumble on top. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, egg and butter.
Add corn and cornbread mix. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: garlic crab
directions: Clean boiled crabs by removing back and other substance.
Break in half and set aside.
In wok or skillet on low heat, place thin slices of fresh garlic (lots).
Add butter (2 sticks of butter for 1 1/2 dozen small to medium crabs); do not burn.
Add garlic powder and parsley.
Add crab parts and continue to baste crabs with garlic-butter sauce.
When crabs are saturated with sauce, they are ready to eat.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Drop in a chunk of butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
If mixture is needed a little thinner for spread add meat stock.
Pack in jar.
Let 1 1/2 headspace. Process pint and 1/2 pint at 10 pounds pressure for 1 hour.
After opening, mix with mayonnaise or sour cream and hard-boiled eggs.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add sherbet and stir until melted. Add fruit; stir and pour into mold. Chill. Serves 12 to 15.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Place tomato wedges, green pepper and onion rings into a shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Pour immediately over vegetables.
Cover tightly and chill.
This will keep several days in refrigerator.
Hot peppers may be added if you like it spicy.

title: mixed vegetable pulad
directions: Wash and soak rice for 15 minutes.
Cut the carrots into small cubes and potatoes into big pieces.
Fry one sliced onion with green cardamon, bay leaves, until light brown.
Add the peas, carrots, rice, coarsely ground spices and salt.
Cook until half tender.
Now add small pieces of peeled potatoes and cook on low fire until tender and water in rice is absorbed.
Sprinkled fried onion slices on the top.
Serve hot.
Serves 9 people.

title: putmans party punch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Freeze to slush, stirring often.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Arrange flattened crescent roll dough, lining bottom and sides of baking dish, making sure to close all cracks between pieces of dough similar to a pie crust.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Remove from oven.
Spread salad dressing over crust.
Add chopped broccoli and cauliflower, then cheese and bacon bits.
Heat to serve or serve cold.
You will love this!
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, pineapple, bread cubes, eggs, onion, horseradish, salt and 2 tablespoons catsup.
Form into long, narrow loaf, about 9 x 5 x 2-inches.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
When done, combine 2 tablespoons catsup with 1/4 cup juice and pour over.

title: scalloped salmon and peas
directions: Melt butter and blend with flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Cook until smooth and thickened.
Add salmon and drained peas. Arrange in greased baking dish in alternate layers with bread crumbs, beginning with salmon mixture and ending with crumbs. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta st. john
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper with turkey sausage cut up into slices.
Boil egg noodles according to package directions.
Add salt and pepper to taste to the onions, bell peppers and sausage. Let cook for about 1/2 hour on low heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cook for 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 can water.
When onions, peppers and sausage are all cooked down, add cooked noodles to mixture.
Serves about 4 adults.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, onion and sugar.
Then, add to broccoli and raisins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle just enough stuffing mix over mixture to cover top and sprinkle poppy seed over this.
Pour melted margarine over this and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared the night before and baked the next day.

title: summertime melon salad
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate, marmalade and liqueur and stir well. Combine melon balls, strawberries and pineapple in a large bowl.
Pour lemonade mixture over fruit, stirring gently. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Spoon fruit mixture in cantaloupe halves. Garnish with mint.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs.
Melt oleo with the chocolate.
Cool slightly.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Add flour, vanilla, and pecans.
Bake in greased 10 x 14-inch pan about 30 minutes at 350.
Cover with icing while still warm.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes; cool well, then peel and shred.
Set aside. Melt butter; add the rest of the ingredients and heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Add to potatoes; stir well and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 7 servings.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Cut English muffins in half; top with sauce, cheese and whatever else is desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: philadelphia cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Add salt to flour. Cut in margarine to flour (like for pie dough). Combine warm water, dry yeast and 1/4 teaspoon sugar and let rise. When risen, add to flour mixture and mix.
Add beaten egg and mix until nice smooth dough.
Place in refrigerator and make filling.

title: southwestern burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, salsa, jalapeno pepper, cumin and salt, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties (1/2-inch thick).
Broil patties over medium coals for 5 minutes or to desired doneness.
Place patties on tomato slices and top with guacamole.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: down home barbecue sauce
directions: In a 1 quart saucepan over medium heat, heat all ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Mm mm good cooking.
From Campbell's Soups.

title: cheddar quick bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar, onion salt, oregano, mustard and cheese.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put ingredients in 9 x 13 pan in order listed. Refrigerate overnight. Do not cover it. Toss before serving.

title: blueberry breeze
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice if desired. Makes two servings.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix shortening, margarine, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Divide dough in half.
Color 1 half with red coloring.
Roll a 4-inch strip, using 1 teaspoon of dough, from each color.
For smooth, even strips, roll on floured board.
Place strips, side by side, pressing lightly together and twist.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bring all to a boil.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water gradually, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes until sauce is clear.
Remove from heat. Beat in lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.

title: jello cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions; cool.
Combine Jell-O and hot water; add Sprite or 7-Up.
Poke holes in top of cake with a wooden spoon handle; pour Jell-O mixture all over top. Mix pudding and Cool Whip together, then ice cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry cream in meringue shells
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until almost stiff.
Gradually add 3/4 cup of sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Shape into cups on baking sheet which has been lined with ungreased brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Turn off heat; cool meringues in oven.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Bring water to a boil.

Stir in rice and salt. Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 30 minutes. Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly. Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in a bowl. Gradually stir in rice mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
If desired, stir in raisins and sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon over top.
Place dish in a pan of water.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: soda cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla, cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour into Pyrex dish and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yummy texas potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large mixing bowl and pour into 9 x 13 inch buttered pan.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake 350 degrees for 60 minutes until golden and bubbly.

title: easy cream cheese appetizer
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
When ready to serve, pour chili sauce over the top of cream cheese and put crackers around dish with a knife.
Another way of serving is add a can of crab to chili sauce.

title: shirley's pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/3 cup water, butter, bread crumbs, onion and poultry seasoning.
Spoon over chops.
Mix soup with the other 1/3 cup water and pour over other.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, water, honey and egg.
Beat with mixer on high speed until well combined.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, pecans, cinnamon, baking soda and allspice; mix well.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake about 12 minutes until cookies or lightly.
Remove from oven.
Let cool for about 2 hours.
Yields about 3 dozen. Store in airtight container.

title: sopa de pasta
directions: Puree tomatoes, onion, garlic and water in a blender.
Strain and set aside.
Heat oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Break up pasta in hands and add to pot.
Stirring constantly until pasta is just turning golden.
Pasta will brown quickly.
Add tomato puree. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add stock.
Bring back to a boil.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 10-15 minutes. Add salt if necessary.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Grind dates and raisins, add orange juice. Cut cherries, pineapple and half of pecans. Add salt, then mix with dates, raisins and orange juice mixture. Place in small bread pan. Cover with wax paper. Press & let stand 48 hours in cool place.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in a large mixing bowl. Combine 1/2 cup lukewarm water, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast; stir well. Pour 1 cup boiling water over creamed mixture; stir until dissolved. Add 1 cup cold water and egg. Stir. Add yeast mixture and stir. Add salt, milk and 6 cups flour; stir well. Let rest 5 minutes. Turn onto remaining flour on a board. Knead until elastic. Place in oiled bowl; turn once to oil top. Cover lightly. Place in refrigerator until needed. Form dough into desired shape rolls. Place on greased pan; let rise until double in size. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stir-fry made simple
directions: In a skillet, add first 4 ingredients and cook on medium heat for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add to chicken the 2 cans of vegetables and cornstarch mixture.
Return to heat and heat until mixture thickens.

title: salsa bean dip
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan, crock-pot or fondue pot; keep warm while serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine together flour, eggs and sugars.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 370° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: citrus-avocado salad
directions: Slice avocado.
Cut oranges and grapefruit into segments. Arrange on lettuce leaf and serve with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough water to equal 1/2 cup. Heat oven to 400°.

title: easy "no-bake" cake
directions: Step 1:
Mix ingredients as directed on back of box.

title: shrimp dip #2
directions: Blend chopped onions with lemon juice and lemon pepper. Mix with other ingredients and
let set for 2 hours or more in refrigerator.

title: corn dogs
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or fork, cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
In a small bowl, combine egg and milk.
Pat frankfurters dry with paper towels.
Insert wooden skewer or popsicle stick in end of each.
Dip frankfurters in batter, being careful to coat all sides.
Drop 1 or 2 at a time into hot oil in deep fryer.
Fry until golden, about 1 minute on each side.
Serve hot!

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, oats, salt, pepper and eggs.
Add onion and 1/2 of tomato sauce.
Form into loaf in 9 x 5 x 3 pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Combine drained pineapple, grapes, bananas, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill overnight. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased souffl dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 400.
Reduce heat to 325 for 45 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip apple slices in it for a great snack.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles; spread with a thin layer of uncooked sausage.
Top with 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Roll (from short end); chill until firm.
Slice each roll into 4 slices.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 32 swirls.

title: milk dunker
directions: Dunk cookies in milk and enjoy!

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into meatballs.
Brown in skillet and set aside.

title: lithuanian kielbossi
directions: Use all fat that is on the meat and grind coarsely.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix well and place in refrigerator overnight. Stiff in washed pork casings.
Refrigerate immediately.

title: mel's seafood medley
directions: Mix together clam juice, sour cream and margarine.
Add enough Ritz crackers to make a sloppy mixture.
Add the juice of 1 lemon. Dice all fish; add to cracker mix.
Put into a deep casserole dish.
Do not overfill, as it will become bubbly while cooking. Sprinkle more crushed Ritz, juice of 1 lemon and paprika on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Any fish may be used such as shrimp, crabs, clams, pollack, etc.
Use your imagination. This is an economical and filling dish.

title: peas pizzicato
directions: Thaw and drain peas (do not cook).
Toss with remaining ingredients; chill overnight.
Garnish with tomatoes and parsley or mint or pimento.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In a large bowl, mix hamburger, egg, 1/4 can cream of mushroom soup, onion, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and garlic.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Form patties out of meat mixture.
Put meat in skillet and cook until done.
Remove meat from pan and drain grease.
Mix all the rest of the soup in to make a gravy.
Place meat back in and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine; mix well.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken and sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fish eye salad
directions: Make a pudding of flour, sugar, pineapple juice, salt and eggs. Heat until thickened; cool.
Mix soup macaronis, fruit, pudding and Cool Whip together.
Chill.

title: granny's home made dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve 3/4 cup of sugar, 2 packages of rapid rise yeast in 2 1/2 cups warm water approximately 100° in bowl and let stand 5 minutes.

title: baked chicken(easy, beginners)
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400 degrees. In the bag, put the flour, salt, pepper, season salt and shake to mix. When the oven has pre-heated, put the butter in the baking pan and place in oven just until melted. Rinse chicken pieces under cold water, shake off excess moisture, then put in bag and shake until coated. Repeat above until all pieces are in the baking pan. Place in oven. Bake for 30 minutes, remove the pan from oven and turn chicken pieces over. Place back in the oven and cook an additional 30-35 minutes. Remove from oven and serve.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put cake mix, flour and jello into mixing bowl and blend well. Add oil, water and strawberries.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Bake in two 9-inch pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost cake with vanilla icing.

title: poppy seed noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
In pan the noodles were boiled in, melt the butter or margarine; add poppy seed and noodles with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat through.

title: pork chops (one-dish meal)
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.

Place pork chops in bottom of baking dish. Slice or quarter potatoes and onions on top of pork chops. Cut carrots in 1-inch slices and put on top of that. Pour mixture of first three ingredients over all. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: semi-nutrigrain bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oats and butter. Press half of the mix into a 9 x 13 greased pan. Mix jam and water; spread over the mix. Add the remaining mix on top and bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Before cutting, cool completely.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt oleo.
Add Karo and brown sugar.
Stir over slow heat until boiling.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn.
Spread in large pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Stir at least every 15 minutes.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into thin strips.
In a skillet over high heat, in 1 teaspoon margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and 1/2 of the onion until meat is done and onions are tender.
Set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup; heat thoroughly.
Reduce heat to very low. Stir in sour cream.
Gently heat thoroughly and serve over noodles.

title: ritz bits snack
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine crackers and nuts in a greased bowl or pan.
Melt oleo, sugar and corn syrup to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour over crackers and nuts and mix well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper.

title: old fitzgerald bourbon balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine crumbs, sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Stir with a large spoon.
Combine the liquids, whiskey and corn syrup. Mix them well with the dry ingredients.
Roll about a tablespoon of dough between the palms of your hands to form a ball. Roll the ball in additional powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Good keepers in storage.
Makes about 48 bourbon balls.

title: lela's pineapple cake icing
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar and boil for 20 minutes.
Add margarine and boil 10 minutes more.
Remove from heat and put pan in a pan of cold water.
Cool, then beat until thickness to spread on cake.

title: pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar on medium speed. Add eggs one at a time. Beat thoroughly after each. Add vanilla and almond extracts and continue mixing. Reduce speed to low and alternately add whipping cream and flour. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake about 1 hour and 20 minutes on 325°.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk, cocoa and vanilla well.
Bring to a boil, on medium heat, for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add oats.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spoon onto waxed paper quickly.
Let cool.
Yields about 16.

title: coconut cream
directions: Boil 1 cup water.
Blend other ingredients with remaining water.
Add
mixture
to
boiling water.
Stir-cook until thick. Chill.
Whip
again in blender for a smoother texture. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add well-beaten eggs, then bananas and beat.
Mix dry ingredients separately and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.

title: cheesy hominy
directions: Place in buttered shallow baking pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Keep warm at 200° until served.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend filling ingredients and pour into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: oven potato salad
directions: Parboil potatoes; slice half of them into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the next 4 ingredients together; spread half of it over potatoes.
Slice rest of potatoes into pan, then add the rest of the cheese mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whamits
directions: Heat last 7 ingredients in microwave until blended, approximately 2 minutes.
Pour cereal, nuts and pretzels into large microwave bowl.
Gently stir spices and margarine mixture into cereal mixture until evenly coated.
Heat on High in microwave for 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Stir frequently until completely cooled.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes 15 cups.

title: unusual squash casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Chop or slice squash, boil about 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup Cheddar cheese to meat mixture and place half in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Add squash, sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese, remaining meat mixture, sour cream and remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Let cool partially; cut into squares.
Serve warm.
May cook 40 minutes in an aluminum pan, if you desire.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning together.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with nacho chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and water in pan on low heat until sugar is dissolved. Boil 3 minutes.
Mix this mixture slowly into well beaten eggs. Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Lay pecan halves on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molasses cake
directions: Stir all together at once.

title: chicken verde
directions: Cook chicken in one lemon slice, 2 tablespoons salt and the bay leaf.
Cool; cut into cubes.
Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Place in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Mix and pour over chicken; top with the grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jo l.'s fruit pizza
directions: Spread softened cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake as directed on package at 325°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with sugar; spread over chilled dough.
Cover with well-drained fruit cocktail and well-drained pineapple.
Sprinkle crushed pecans over all.
Chill and serve in wedges.

title: mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 7 ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes; cool completely.

title: parmesan zucchini strips
directions: In bowl, combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip zucchini in egg substitute and then into crumb mixture.
Place on nonstick pan.
Bake at 450° for 20-25 minutes until golden brown.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Spread apples in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple on top of apples.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit filling. Layer nuts and coconut over top of cake mix.
Pour butter over top of all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Melt sugar and butter to an almost caramelized stage over medium heat. Beat egg yolks. Shake up flour with part of the milk. Pour into sugar and butter mixture and cook until thick and bubbly.
Pour into baked pie shells. Top with meringue and brown.

title: beef with broccoli
directions: Slice beef into thin strips in large pan.
Cook in oil with garlic until beef is brown.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: beef or venison marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Slice 2 lb. of beef or deer meat in 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle meat with a little garlic and pepper, the more garlic and pepper the more spicy it will be. Pound meat with meat mallet.
Place in bowl of marinade, and store in refrigerator.
Stir 3 or 4 times within the next 24 hours. Place in dehydrator or slow baking oven.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the egg yolks, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Crumble vanilla wafers in pie plate and place whole wafers around sides of pie plate.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Chill before serving.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade together a few minutes and add Cool Whip. Whip until fluffy. Pour in crust and chill around 4 hours.

title: cherried cranberries
directions: Place all ingredients in a very large pan.
Cover and boil very gently over low heat for 15 minutes.
Do not remove cover. Remove from heat and set aside until completely cool.
Spoon into jars.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: beets and apples
directions: Cut top from beets (leave 1-inch of stem). Cook beets in boiling salt water for 15 to 20 minutes, until just tender. Drain, reserving 2 cups of the liquid.
Cool beets until you can slip off skins.
Cut into thin slices.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Let set overnight (refrigerated).
Re-blend and serve.

title: stickie buns
directions: Slowly heat the first 6 ingredients and mix together in saucepan (do not bring to a boil). Set aside.
Thaw and break up the first loaf of bread in a greased cake pan.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Pour sauce over top.
Break up second loaf over top of sauce. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Flip onto wax paper to cool.

title: austrian potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and hard-boil eggs.
Cut potatoes as for potato salad.
Put in a large bowl.
Dice eggs and onion and mix with potatoes.
Add the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Chop pickles into mixture and sprinkle sugar over all.
Mix. Add dill weed, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.
(This is even better the second day.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain well crushed pineapple.
Chop fine bell pepper.
Cream well cream cheese, onion and seasoning salt.
Mix well with pineapple and pepper.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve with crackers or bagels.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: More flour may be added to make dough handle easily.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves for 3 minutes in boiling, salted water. Drain; dry.
Combine ground beef, onion, rice and seasonings.
Put about 1/4 cup on each cabbage leaf.
Roll and fasten with wooden toothpick.
Place rolls close together in greased baking dish. Brush rolls with butter and pour tomato juice over them.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° until cabbage leaves are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove wooden picks before serving.

title: broccoli cheese salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, cheese and onion and mix in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Stir into broccoli mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: microwave pizza burgers
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Add onion and cover with lid.
Cook on High (max power) 4 minutes. Stir to break up meat into small pieces.
Continue to cook on High for 1 or 2 minutes more. Drain fat.
Stir in salt, pepper, cinnamon and pizza sauce.
Cook, covered, on High 5 to 6 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Arrange 4 bottom halves of buns on micro-proof plate.
Spoon on half meat mixture.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Top with bun tops.
Cook on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts. Repeat with other buns.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crispix mock mochi crunch
directions: Heat butter, sugar, oil, corn syrup and shoyu sauce in saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Pour mixture over cereal and mix well.
Add furikake and again mix until well coated.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring well, every 15 minutes.
Stir for another 2 to 3 minutes while cooling.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add this to cream.
Mix and add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water (5 minutes); drain. Combine soup and sour cream; fold in drained squash and onion.
In bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2 pinch pan, spread margarine mixed with 1/2 stuffing mix.
Spread vegetable mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables.
Bake on 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Saute onions in butter.
Add soup, milk, shredded cheese and seasonings. Stir until cheese melts. Remove bones from salmon and thaw peas slightly to separate. Combine macaroni, sauce, salmon and peas.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet along with green pepper and onion.
When done, drain grease well.
Add taco seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Cook until just heated.
Crush bag of chips and put 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture on top of chips and the 1/2 of cheeses.
Repeat with meat mixture and cheese and top with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Top off with lettuce, tomato, sour cream, taco sauce or your favorite taco toppings.

title: "say cheese" banana cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together 2 1/4 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter and white sugar, slowly adding the eggs, one at a time.
In another bowl, mash the bananas and blend well with 1/2 cup Ricotta cheese (reserve other 1/2 cup of Ricotta for the topping).
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture, alternating with the mashed bananas.
Blend gently just until mixed.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients (picante sauce is optional; will make recipe very hot!), stirring until cheese sauce is smooth.
Add the chilies and pimentos to the sauce.
Brown the ground beef; drain fat.
Remove from heat and add onion and cheese.
Fill flour tortillas with beef mixture.
Roll up and place in greased oblong pan.
Pour cheese mixture over tortillas.
Cover and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Add baking soda and milk to mixture.
Stir in flour and rhubarb (cut in small pieces). Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13 pan.

title: swiss chocolate squares
directions: Combine water, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 1/2 squares chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in combined flour and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: colonial dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, onion and 2 tablespoons of the vinegar in a blender or mix with electric mixer on medium speed. Add oil slowly (on low).
This will be thick.
Add remaining vinegar and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Stir in celery seed and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup salted water for 5 minutes.
Add soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into buttered baking dish.
(Can leave refrigerated overnight.)
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Preheat oven and bake 30 minutes, 50 minutes if casserole was refrigerated.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Heat cranberry juice to boiling; remove from heat.
Add to gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Refrigerate until of the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled 1-quart mold or 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold and serve on crisp greens with fresh orange twists for trim.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts and press in large pie plate.
Brown slightly in 350° oven.
Cream Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread evenly over cool crust.
Mix milk with pudding and cream well.
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill until firm (can be frozen).

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken and bone; save broth.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat; stir until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth; heat to boiling.
Stir constantly and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in wine and nutmeg; add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Place layers of noodles, broccoli and chicken in ungreased baking dish. Pour sauce over layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil in oven until golden.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mexican dip(50 servings)
directions: Brown the ground round in skillet. Chop cheese into cubes. Spray large crock-pot with oil. Add ground round, sauces and black beans. Stir. Cook on low all day. Serve with tortilla chips, black olives, sour cream and guacamole. Add your own toppings. Makes 50 servings, but you can reduce recipe as needed.

title: pralines
directions: Toast 2 cups of pecans for 5 minutes in 350° oven.
Place 1 cup of sugar in small pot.
Cook on low heat and stir until melted. While this is cooking, place 2 cups of sugar and milk in a large pot and cook until it is about to come to a boil.
Pour melted sugar into milk and sugar while stirring.
Cook to a soft boil (238°), then drop into cold water to see if it forms a firm ball. Take off the heat.
Add salt, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until this begins to thicken.
Drop a tablespoon at a time onto aluminum foil and let dry.
Peel off foil and store pralines.

title: carolina red beans and rice
directions: Drain beans early on the morning after soaking.
In a large cooking pot or kettle, place beans in 1 gallon of water; add ham bone, bay leaves, sugar, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for four hours.
While beans are simmering, fry onion, celery, pepper, garlic and parsley in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes and cook until slightly thick. Add to simmering beans; red beans should really simmer all day. Add water, if necessary.
Continue cooking.
Remove bay leaves and serve over fluffy white rice.
Top each bowl with a piece of cooked sausage.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Hot French bread and a green salad is great with this.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar replacement.
Add applesauce and water, stirring to mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves in sifter.
Sift dry ingredients into applesauce mixture; stir to blend.
Fold in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Or microwave, placing 6 to 8 cookies on waxed paper.
Cook on Low for 3 to 4 minutes or until tops are set. Yields 30 cookies.
Exchange:
1 cookie - 1/2 fruit and 1/5 fat.

title: easy crabmeat spread
directions: Drain crabmeat and squeeze lemon juice over.
Mix together crabmeat and cocktail sauce.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: marshmallow surprise
directions: Place marshmallows in a bowl and add drained pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Stir in sour cream to make a creamy mixture, only add just enough.
Sprinkle sugar lightly over mixture and stir in.
Let sit for 1/2 hour in the refrigerator to harden and blend the flavors.
Great for a quick and light dessert, especially good in the summer.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water. Add ice cream in small amounts until melted. Add pineapple and nuts. Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Split muffins.
Spread each half with pizza sauce.
Add some salami and
pepperoni;
cover
with
each
cheese.
Place under broiler or in oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: spud nuts
directions: Mix together and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and cover with damp cloth to rise.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut doughnuts out; let rise, then fry in 1 quart of oil.

title: homestead corn pudding(8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Scald milk in large saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in cornmeal, sugar and salt.
Place over medium-high heat and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring constantly, 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in corn.
Gradually add egg, stirring vigorously.
Add butter, vanilla and baking powder and blend well. Turn into prepared dish.
Bake until set, about 45 to 50 minutes. Serve hot.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put nuts and coconut in pan. Prepare cake mix by using oil, water and eggs.
Pour mixture over nuts and coconut.
Beat sugar, margarine and cream cheese well. Pour over cake.
Smooth as evenly as possible.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Add whipped topping and vanilla. Tear angel food cake into small pieces. Mix strawberries and glaze together in a bowl. Put a layer of cake first in a large bowl, then follow with a layer of cream cheese mixture, then strawberry glaze mix. Continue layers in this manner. Spread cream cheese mixture on top and refrigerate.

title: corn chowder
directions: Boil onion in 1 cup of water.
Add potato and boil until done. Add more water, a little at a time, to prevent potato from burning down.
Do not drain.
Add corn, cream-style corn, light cream and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: popcorn rolls
directions: Bring corn
syrup,
butter,
water, confectioners sugar and marshmallows to boil
or until everything is melted.
Pour over popcorn.
Grease hands and form popcorn balls.

title: butterscotch 'n marshmallow crispies
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan or a rather large pan with spray margarine.
Melt margarine and marshmallows in a saucepan slowly on the stove (or in a microwave in a large microwave dish; I use a 4-quart glass casserole dish).
Melt butter first, then dump marshmallows on top and melt them.
Keep an eye on these as they puff up and can overflow.
Marshmallows are done if you can take a spoon and squish them together without many lumps.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Crumble all cookies except 5.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbled cookies.
Place in glass baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 bowl of Cool Whip until creamy.
Pour over cookie crust.
Follow directions on pudding mix.
Layer over cream cheese layer.
Top with layer of Cool Whip and crumble the 5 cookies on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fudge "no bake" cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a pan.
After it comes to a boil, boil 1 minute by the clock.
Remove from heat.
Add other 4 ingredients all at once; mix until blended.
While still hot, drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: sour cream(this makes a great dip for chips or a relish tray.)
directions: You can cheat and just open two cans of cranberries or you can buy cranberries in packages.
If you decide on buying the packaged cranberries, follow the directions on the package.
It is just a matter of heating the cranberries with water and sugar.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Mix together the buttermilk and soda.
Beat together the eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bring to a boil 1 stick margarine, 1 cup water, the oil and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Stir in dry ingredients, then egg mixture, then buttermilk mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple cranberry crispy
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples sliced thin. Arrange apples in buttered baking dish (about 10 x 6 x 2-inches). Spoon cranberry sauce over apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Stir rolled oats with cinnamon. Stir rolled oats, flour and brown sugar together. Cut in butter until evenly mixed and crumbly. Sprinkle over cranberry layer. Bake in moderate oven at 350° until apples are cooked through and top is lightly browned, about 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with cream if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Brush a 3-quart shallow baking dish with melted butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread smoothly into dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Put beans in large pot; add water and cook about 1 hour.
Add ham, onion, celery, carrots and soup; salt and pepper to taste.
Add more water if necessary. Continue cooking until beans are tender.

title: chicken-vegetable jambalaya
directions: Prepare Rice-a-Roni according to package directions, except add 2 3/4 cups water with flavoring packet.
Add chicken and vegetables. Simmer until liquid cooks away, about 20 to 30 minutes. Easy and good.

title: fruit salad(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Mix ingredients together in very large bowl and chill.
Pecans may be added if desired. Any fruits may be substituted.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Pour pecans into pie shells.
Beat all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 350 degrees for 50 - 60
minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in bowl first 5 ingredients, then mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread on top of salad then top with grated cheese. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spread 1 can crescent rolls on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the vegetables, soup and chicken.
Put in pan.
Put the other can of rolls on top and bake at 400° until golden brown. Can use canned vegetables instead of frozen.
This is better if you boil the frozen vegetables first.

title: molded ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in water.
Add pineapple and cool. When slightly thickened, add nuts, oranges, coconut and sour cream.
Blend and chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Mix corn muffin mix, egg and milk until moistened; set aside. Mix ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic in an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Microwave on High until meat loses its pink color, 5 to 9 minutes, stirring once to break up meat.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, tomato paste, chili powder and salt.
Spread muffin mix over the top; bake according to muffin directions.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples.
Boil sugar, water, cinnamon and butter.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Beat egg yolks slightly and combine with the 3/4 cup cold milk.
Add to dry ingredients, forming a smooth paste.
Add warm milk slowly and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add butter and when mixture is cool, add vanilla.
A little yellow coloring may be added for a stronger banana flavoring. Cool, stirring occasionally to prevent crust from forming.
When cool, cover and keep in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: children's play dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients in pan.
Add oil, water and coloring and stir together.
Cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes, or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Don't overcook.
Turn out and knead until cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, saute the carrot, onion and garlic over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add broth, cabbage, beans, tomato paste, basil, oregano and salt; bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until beans are tender.
Stir in zucchini and heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, stir together chicken, celery, rice, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, salt, water chestnuts, soup and boiled eggs.
Drizzle melted butter over mixture.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can be served on bed of lettuce or on hot rolls or bread.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: hamburger steak in mushroom gravy
directions: Combine meat with egg, crumbs and seasonings, and half the onion soup mix.
Shape into patties and fry in the cooking oil. Remove the browned hamburgers.
Add flour to frypan and stir while it browns lightly.
Blend in liquid, stirring vigorously until smooth.
Stir in remaining onion soup mix and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Return meat to skillet and cook slowly 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: sausage brunch casserole #3
directions: Brown sausage and onions; drain.
Mix flour, Parmesan, salt and basil in a small bowl.
Mix eggs and milk in the blender.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture and blend well in blender.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Place sausage in pan and put half of pimento on top.
Top with all of the spinach.
Pour the egg mixture on top. Sprinkle top with Provolone cheese and pimento.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes (if glass, bake at 400°).

title: carolyn's shrimp casserole
directions: Clean duck cavity well.
Salt and pepper duck.
Coat the duck in and out with orange marmalade.
Oil the bottom of Dutch oven. Saute onions and add parsley.
Add duck and bake for 30 minutes, uncovered, at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Add water (about 1-inch) and cover.
Return to oven and bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: concrete pie
directions: You will need a well-greased pie dish.

title: laurel's chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels, butter and cream until creamy consistency. Cool.
Shape when nearly cooled.
Place on four pecans, about size of 50 cent piece.
Melt candy bar and paraffin.
Cook.
Dip caramel turtles into the chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: evelyn's vegetable-oat patties
directions: Place all ingredients except oatmeal in blender and blend well. Pour into bowl and add 1 to 1 1/2 cups uncooked oatmeal; mix well. Add a little at a time until mixture is thick.
Let stand until liquid is absorbed and mixture holds together.
(May be mixed in evening and refrigerated overnight.)
Spray frypan with Pam; form mixture into patties, being sure they aren't too thick.
Brown on both sides.
May be used for "burgers" or as patties with gravy as entree.
These freeze well.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Heat margarine and chocolate just until melted, then add yolks, sugar and vanilla; let cool.
Fold in egg whites.

title: homestyle baked beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the bacon.
Let cook for approximately 30 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
The bacon may be done either of two ways.
It may be cooked otherwise and two pieces be crumbled into the finished dish with the other pieces lying on top.
Or, if you prefer, the bacon may be cooked on top of the beans as they cook.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon batter into two well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beat well.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn off oven and partially open oven door for 30 minutes.
Take out and cool at room temperature.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill 8 hours.
Graham cracker crust should be in spring-form pan.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve strawberry Jell-O, use only 1 cup water, add cranberry relish.
Pour in oiled mold, chill until firm. In medium bowl prepare lime Jell-O, add food color, chill until partially set.

title: pineapple angel pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple, lemon juice and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gradually add a little of the hot pineapple mixture to the egg yolks, then put the hot mixture in saucepan. Cook 1 to 2 minutes more. Chill. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell. Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Serve.

title: salsa mac
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess fat if any.
Add water, picante sauce and shells.
Bring to a boil.
Allow to boil until shells are tender.
Most of the water will be absorbed.
Add cheese sauce and stir.

title: caesar salad
directions: To prepare romaine, rinse and drain well; break into bite size pieces.
Place in large plastic bag and chill in refrigerator at least one hour or longer before serving.

title: quick rice casserole
directions: Place rice in casserole dish.
Pour soup and consomme in. Stir.
Cut margarine up on top.
Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Do not cover while cooking.

title: tex mex casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with tortilla chips. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour in mixture.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake until it bubbles around sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, alternating with flour.
Add flavor.
Turn oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Cook cake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Do not preheat oven.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Combine Shredded Wheat and boiling water.
Add following in the order given and mix well while adding: 1/2 cup buttermilk, honey, shortening, sugar, eggs, baking soda, remaining buttermilk, Bran Buds and flour.
Store in refrigerator up to 5 weeks.
Or place in muffin tins and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: orange waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of salad greens, if desired.
Yields approximately 5 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: coffee pudding cake
directions: Sift flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons Espresso powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Mix milk, cream, butter and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until blended well.
Spread batter in 8-inch cake pan.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 1 teaspoon Espresso coffee powder.
Sprinkle over batter.
Mix brandy and hot water.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until cake is set.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix flour and butter; add shredded cheese.
Roll out 1/4 inch thickness.
Brush with beaten egg.
As soon as they are taken out of the oven, sprinkle with salt.
Preheat oven to 425° and bake for 12 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, 1/3 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, with fork, combine egg, milk, oil and flour.
Mix until well blended.
Add blueberries.
Pour into muffin cups.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly on muffins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sift together both flours, soda and salt into small bowl.
Set aside. Combine bananas and buttermilk; set aside.
Cream butter, oil, sugars and vanilla in mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Scrape down bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix on medium for 10 seconds, then scrape down each time.
Add 1/3 of dry ingredients and mix on low speed for 8 seconds.
Scrape.
Add 1/2 banana mixture and mix 10 seconds.
Scrape.
Add 1/3 dry ingredients and mix; scrape.
Add remaining banana; mix and scrape.
Add the last of dry ingredients and mix; scrape.
Do not overmix.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until top is golden and springs back to touch.
Cool and eat.
Frosting not needed.

title: tamale balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt, yeast, melted butter, and add luke warm water.
Add flour and knead until smooth.
Let raise until double in size, about 1 1/2 - 2 hours.

title: corn custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating.
Add flour.
