Add slowly to scalded milk.
Combine with 1 cup corn and salt.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cream cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: yeast biscuits *
directions: Mix together yeast, warm water and sugar.
Let set awhile. Mix all ingredients together and knead well.
Store in refrigerator.
Roll out amount needed.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Peel zucchini and mix with onions, pepper and salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain in colander under cold water.
Mix other ingredients and cook until well mixed.
Add drained vegetables and cook 30 minutes.
Seal hot.
You can add can of pimiento when ready to seal.
Pimiento and mustard seed are optional.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and put in bread pan.
Place in pan of water. Bake, uncovered, until browned, then cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: spiced pumpkin pie
directions: Roll pastry on floured surface to circle 1 inch larger than inverted pie pan.
Ease pastry into pan; trim and flute edge.
Beat pumpkin, evaporated milk and eggs in medium bowl; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet or paella pan, heat oil and saute garlic, onion and green pepper for 3 minutes (until softened).
Add remaining ingredients (except shrimp).
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Quickly add shrimp, cover and cook 5 minutes longer, or until rice is tender and shrimp have turned pink.
Toss with a fork to fluff rice and distribute shrimp.
Serves 4.

title: hot vidalia dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together the chopped onions, shredded sharp cheese and the mayo.
Pour into an ungreased quiche pan or comparable Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle generously with paprika. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Place a triple layer of paper towels across the top of the dish to absorb any oil that surfaces.
Serve hot with crostini, Italian toast or a favorite savory cracker.
Provides 18 light servings or 10 generous servings.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Halve chicken, cleaned.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Mix olive oil, oregano, lemon juice, garlic and parsley thoroughly.
Brush chicken generously with this mixture.
Place on grill with low heat.
Frequently brush with mixture to prevent dryness.
Grill about twenty minutes each side or until brown and tender.
When done, pour balance of liquid over chicken and serve very hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones and cut up chicken meat.
Cook onion and pepper in margarine about 10 minutes. Do not brown.
Mix with next 3 ingredients.
Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas.
Pour over them half the chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with half the grated cheese.
Pour remaining mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook beef until done.
Cool.
Grind.
Wash, pare, core and grind apples.
Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Pack hot into jars.
Process in pints and quarts 20 minutes at 10 pounds pressure or 1 1/2 hours in boiling water bath.
Also freezes well. I measure ground meat and ground apples by the cup and have double the amount of apples as meat.

title: orange chicken
directions: Saute onion in oil; add chicken breasts and brown on both sides.
Add soups with water and pour over chicken.
Simmer on low heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
This may be cooked in a crock-pot or electric skillet.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Prepare chicken by cooking and chopping.
Mix equal parts of sour cream and mayonnaise.
Prepare the grapes by splitting in half.
Mix nuts and grapes into the chicken mix and serve with cracker, rolls or make sandwiches.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Soak cucumbers 12 to 14 hours in lime. Wash and soak 4 hours in salt water.
Wash and soak in cold water for 2 hours. Put cucumbers in hot alum water. Let boil. Wash in boiling water.

title: seafood and pasta
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in large black skillet.
Add green onions, garlic, salt and cajun seasoning.
Stir well, approximately one minute.
Add seafood and saute until done.
Add mushrooms, seafood stock and remaining margarine.
Cook until all ingredients are mixed and margarine is melted.
Serve over pasta and with lots of French bread.
Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients until frothy. Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Add dry ingredient mixture to wet mixture in parts. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough into small balls. Roll balls into a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken until done, about 45 minutes.
Cool and remove chicken from fat and bones.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
Fry bacon, then remove from skillet.
Drain and crumble. Fry onions in bacon drippings until soft and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except okra.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours or use crock-pot on low heat for 4 to 6 hours.
One hour before serving, add okra.
Serve over bed of rice.
(Leftovers can be frozen.) Makes 6 large servings.

title: spaghetti red
directions: Brown meat with onions, bell pepper, onion and celery. Add tomato sauce, ketchup and seasonings and let simmer while spaghetti cooks. Mix it all together and bake in a 9 x 13 dish for 30 minutes, covered, at 350°. Remove foil and cook an additional 15 minutes. May be frozen.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the peanut butter and confectioners sugar with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle 3/4 of this on bottom of baked crust.
Prepare cooked pudding. Pour while warm over prepared shell.
Beat egg whites. Add sugar for meringue.
Spread over pie. Sprinkle remainder of crumbs over top.
Brown 5 minutes in 375° oven. Serve warm or chilled.

title: peanut-chocolate haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter; stir.
Add noodles.
Stir again.
Drop clusters on wax paper.
Cool.

title: standard yellow cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to the creamy butter and sugar mixture.
Add egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in three layer pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill.
Yields about 3 cups.
Serve with assorted crackers or remove center of Hawaiian bread and tear into bite size pieces.
Stuff hull of bread with dip and serve with torn bread pieces.

title: butterscotch crunch cookies
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Blend in lard then add rest of ingredients and mix until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Use beater.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, flavoring and oil.
Beat well together and add baking powder to flour, then add gradually to mixture.
Grease apple strudel pan.
Cook for 10 minutes in a 400° oven (test with toothpick).
After cools, slice 1/2-inch thick.
Put back in pan; put back in oven just to toast.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck, onion and garlic powder.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano, salt, pepper and basil.
Simmer ingredients, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir often.
Cook 8 ounces of spaghetti, broken up.
Then drain and stir in meat sauce.

title: waikiki meat balls(sweet and sour)
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape into bite-size balls.
Heat oil in a large skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs.
Keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese, then crackers.
Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into a loaf pan and cover with two strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour over all one (8 ounce) can of Hunt's tomato sauce.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute rice and mushrooms in butter.
Add chopped onion and liquid.
Add salt, as desired.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with parsley and serve.

title: spotted dog
directions: Heat the oven to 450°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Put the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add the buttermilk and egg.
Mix the flour into the liquid until a soft dough forms.
Stir in the currants.
Turn the dough onto a floured board and knead several times, then shape into a large ball.
Transfer to the baking sheet.
With a sharp knife, cut an "x" into the dough.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce the oven temperature to 400° and bake until the bread is cooked through, 30 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.

title: duncan hines cherry cheesecake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Divide batter in half and pour half into a 9x13 greased
pan.
Bake and cool. Leave in
pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Spray pan with Pam.
Add meat mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: company beef stew
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, sauce, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Combine macaroni and beef mixture in a casserole.
Season to taste.
Spoon (gently) mushroom soup into mixture, lifting from bottom.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(This freezes well.)
Will make 2 medium size casseroles.

title: grandma kleiner's buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Then add slowly buttermilk.
Add spices and mix.
Add raisins and nuts and flour until pretty thick.
Bake in a 350° oven until tests done, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: moravian sugar cakes
directions: Cook 2 medium large potatoes and save water.
Mash potatoes (do not add milk).
Soften yeast in 1 cup warm potato water.
Mix together sugar, salt, eggs and 1 cup melted butter.
Gradually beat in mashed potatoes.
Add 1 cup flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in yeast and beat in enough flour to form a light soft dough.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 2 hours.
Punch down dough and divide into 3 (9-inch) square or 9-inch round cake pans.
Cover; let rise until doubled.
Blend brown sugar and cinnamon.
Make indentations about 1-inch apart.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over top, then drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gene's butter herb baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 by 9 inch pan, melt butter. Mix all the above ingredients together except fish.
Dip fish in butter and then crumb mixture.
Bake near center of oven for 25 to 30 minutes until tender or fish flakes with fork.
Any fish fillet will work; especially good with Wisconsin Walleye or Bluegill.

title: reception salad
directions: Drain
juice
from
pineapple and heat juice.
Dissolve jello in
juice
and let cool.
Cream the cheese with a little milk
and mashed
pimento.
Add celery, pineapple, mayonnaise and
nuts. Let
mixture thicken, then fold in cream which has been whipped stiff.
Serves 15.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in chopped pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Scatter halves over top and bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 45 minutes or until filling is set and the pastry is browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: butter mints
directions: Knead all ingredients together with
hands until mixed well. Press into small balls and then press flat.
These freeze well.

title: pan cream puffs
directions: Boil water and butter; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup flour; stir.
Add 1 egg at a time; stir each through.
Spray pan with Pam (no Teflon pans).
Spread mixture in pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese; spread on mixture.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 to 200 cookies.

title: lemon herbed salmon
directions: In a bowl, combine bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, cheese, thyme, lemon peel and salt.
Mix well.
Add 4 tablespoons butter and toss lightly to coat.
Set aside.
Pat salmon dry.

title: refrigerated cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion.
Heat to boiling point other ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Put into jar and close tightly.
Refrigerate.
Will keep about 1 week.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, cream of mushroom soup, milk and half can of French fried onions in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Top with other half of French fried onions.
Bake 5 more minutes and serve hot.

title: oceania chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, salt, celery salt, garlic salt and nutmeg in paper bag.
Use to coat chicken on all sides. Heat butter in a large skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Place chicken in a large casserole.

title: busy day macaroni
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, crumble ground beef. Microwave for 5 minutes at High.
Stir twice to break up ground beef.
Drain fat. Add sauce, uncooked macaroni and water to casserole.
Cover. Microwave for 13 minutes at High.
Stir once.
Sprinkle cheese on top; let stand covered 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir flour, soda and 1 teaspoon salt together.
Add to egg mixture.
Shape into balls; roll in bowl of granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Add chocolate star to top of each cookie while it is still hot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add milk and stir.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour in bacon drippings and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and bake in an iron skillet for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: nana pearl's casserole
directions: Dot potatoes with oleo.
Sprinkle hamburg over potatoes and top with soup.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter preacher cookies
directions: Place butter, sugar and milk in 2-quart pan. Bring to a full rolling boil. Remove from heat. Let set 1 minute. Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Beat until it begins to stiffen. Drop on waxed paper.

title: connie's icebox dessert
directions: Spread the cookie dough in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Mix together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar; spread on baked cookie crust.
Mix together the pudding and milk; spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with crushed nuts as a nice garnish.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: german gingerbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly; save 1 cup for topping. Add all other dry ingredients together, then add milk and egg batter; the mixture will not be smooth.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: colonial innkeeper's pie
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Add
2/3 cup sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove and stir in 1/4 cup butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Let cool.
Blend flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/4 cup butter, milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Gently spoon chocolate mixture over batter.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini dill pickles
directions: Cut squash lengthwise into sticks of approximate size for canning.
Combine garlic, salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Place two garlic cloves in each hot sterilized jar. Arrange zucchini sticks in jars; add dill and peppercorns and top with grape leaves.
Pour in hot pickling juice.
Seal and process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs; drain.
Beat eggs.
Fold in soup, milk, mayo and cheeses; mix well.
Fold in cooked broccoli. Salt and pepper as needed.
Crunch Ritz crackers.
Set aside.
Pour mixture in casserole dish.
Spread crackers on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: old el paso guacamole
directions: Prepare all ingredients.
In a medium bowl, carefully mix all ingredients.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Add salt, vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add milk, apples and nuts. Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Blend.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan. Pour glaze over bread, letting it drip down the sides.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients with fork in large bowl and roll out between wax paper.
If dough seems tough, add teaspoon of cold milk.
This makes 2 crusts.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream, vanilla, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit pie(blueberry)
directions: Mix together from jello down and cook to boiling.
Pour over berries in cooked pie crust.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles; mix in tuna, soup, cheese, milk, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Slightly crush potato chips and put them about 1/4-inch thick on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Marinate strips of steak for 30 minutes in ingredients.
Heat a little oil in skillet and brown meat.
Add water to make gravy, then add onion and green pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes or longer. Serve over rice.

title: apple star bread
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: In 3 qt. sauce pan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in garlic, chili powder, cumin and crushed red pepper; cook 30 seconds. Stir in beans, broth and 2 cups water; heat to boiling over high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: chris' peanut butter cups(kid recipe)
directions: Mix peanut butter cookie mix as directed on box.
Divide dough into 36 balls which are the size of a walnut.
Place in greased small muffin tins.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place a peanut butter cup in center of each ball.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and place in refrigerator.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 36.

title: cooking light corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil. Add onions; cook for 5 minutes.
Add celery, red peppers, garlic and cumin.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken stock, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add corn and potatoes; return to simmer and cook until vegetables are tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Place cornstarch in small bowl.
Slowly add evaporated milk, stirring until smooth.
Stir into soup. Cook, stirring, until thickened about 2 minutes. Discard bay leaf. Season with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups. Serves 6.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk in saucepan until thick.
Cool until cold. Add remaining ingredients and beat about 10 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add chili and enchilada sauce.
Heat together until mixture simmers.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Alternate layers of tortillas, chili mixture, onions and cheese.
Bake, covered, for 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven. Uncover the last 15 minutes.
Let casserole sit at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: amaretti(italian macaroons)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cover a large cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Butter and flour it lightly and set aside.
Grind almonds in food processor with the granulated sugar.
Blend the egg whites and almond flavoring into the mixture, while processor is running.
The batter should have the consistency of soft dough.

title: garlic sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse. Toss with margarine.
Add sour cream and seasonings.
You can vary amount of sour cream according to your family's preference. Serves 6.

title: wedding punch
directions: Pour ginger ale over ice cream mix.
Serves 30.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and dip with Tostitos.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate or casserole dish; put veggies (and meat if desired) and cheese in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl until smooth.
Pour into dish (over veggies); sprinkle with cheese on top and bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Freezes great; heats up in microwave for make ahead dish.

title: apple cake (old english)
directions: Refrigerate 1 hour diced apples, walnuts, sugar and cinnamon. Mix together the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, eggs, oil and juice of orange.
Mix well.
Grease tube pan.
Pour part of cake mix in first, then alternate apple mix and cake mix, ending with apple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
No need for icing.

title: ooey gooey coffee cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Put in greased and floured pan. Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over base mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Watch closely because the cake will brown fast.

title: potatoes and pork chops
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Slice onion.
Put half of the potatoes and onion into a greased baking dish or casserole; salt and pepper to taste.
Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Put on top of potatoes and cover with remaining potatoes and onion.
Salt and pepper.
Using drippings left in the frying pan, add flour, bouillon cube, water and season.
Let come to a boil, then pour over pork chops and potatoes; cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick (stirring constantly).
Then add margarine and vanilla. Great with biscuits.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and vanilla and beating well after each addition.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tri-color vegetables with cheese
directions: In
a
12-inch	Dutch
oven combine water, cauliflower, broccoli,
squash and tarragon.
Cover.
Place 14 coals on top and 12 coals on the bottom.
Cook 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and onions over vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together 3 times.
Return to sifter. Beat butter and shortening until creamy.
Gradually add cup of sugar; continue to beat.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift 1/4 flour mixture over molasses mixture.
Stir and repeat until all flour mixture is used.
Shape dough into large marble size balls. Roll balls in extra sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Stir in corn, cornmeal, flour, salt and sugar.
Whip egg whites until stiff and glossy.
Fold in 1/3 of them to lighten batter.
Then fold in remainder, gently. Heat oil (about 4 to 6 cups in a Dutch oven) to 375°.
Drop in dollops (ice cream scoop can be used) and fry until golden. Drain.
Keep warm at 250°.
Dust with confectioners sugar or drizzle with warm maple syrup.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown beef until crumbly in fat.
Add remaining ingredients rinsing cans with the 1 1/2 cups water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then cover with chow mein noodles and bake 15 minutes more.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add egg and water.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator in covered container.
Use as needed. Will keep for several days.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift in large bowl sugar and flour.
In sauce pan mix cocoa, margarine and water, bring to a rapid boil and pour into flour mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and mix well.
Pour in a long greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before the cake is to come out of oven, start preparation for icing.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon and combine with all ingredients, except parsley.
Chill several hours.
Roll into ball, then roll into parsley.
Serve surrounded by crackers.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Wash wings and paper towel dry; salt and pepper to taste. Coat in flour once or twice.
Deep fry in vegetable oil.
Mix 2 parts hot sauce to 1 part butter.
Dip wings in sauce, the hotter you like them the more times you dip the wings.
Serve with Blue cheese dressing and celery sticks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and zucchini.
Add all the rest of the ingredients and blend.
Grease loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve.

title: custard pie
directions: Make pastry for one-crust pie.
Build up high fluted edge. Beat the remaining ingredients together.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake just until a silver knife inserted into side comes out clean.
The center may still look soft, but will set later. Too long baking makes custard watery.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° to finish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be baked at 425° for same time.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, grated cheese, lemon juice, curry powder, salt,
pepper and wine.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; saute onion in butter and add ham to eggs.
Add crackers to onion.
Cream squash.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° twenty to thirty minutes.
When almost done, add grated cheese to cover top.

title: pineapple upside-down ham loaf
directions: Combine brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Blend until smooth. Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Place pineapple slices in a row in brown sugar mixture.
Put a cherry in center of each. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon on top of pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain off excess drippings.
Invert onto service platter.
Serves about 8.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Dredge with flour and brown in small amount of oil.
Insert 1 clove into each chop and place in casserole. Pour excess fat from browning pan, then add water, sugar, bay leaf, sour cream and vinegar.
Stir together and pour over chops.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bake in greased casserole in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix hamburger (uncooked), spices and refried beans.
Put 4 uncooked noodles in 13 x 9-inch pan and spread 1/2 meat/bean mixture over top.
Repeat.
Put remaining 4 noodles on top. Combine water and salsa and put over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix onions, sour cream and olives. When lasagne is done, spoon mixture over top.
Top with 1 cup shredded Jack cheese and bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: plain pastry(my most used pastry; never fails)
directions: Cheese pastry is excellent for apple or cherry pie.
In making cheese
pastry,
use
Plain
Pastry
recipe increasing shortening by
1 tablespoon.
Add 1/3 cup grated sharp cheese. (An aged cheese is best for this.) Stir the grated cheese into the shortening-flour mixture
and continue mixing as for Plain Pastry.

title: gingered rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb with next 3 ingredients in a large saucepan. Let stand about 15 minutes or until sugar is moistened by juice. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until thick and clear, 12 to 15 minutes.
Skim off foam.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Ladle into hot scalded jars and seal.
Makes three 1/2 pints.

title: fruit cobbler pie
directions: Combine sweetened fruit and butter.
Place half in medium pan or bowl.
Cover with pie crust, brown in 400° oven.
Repeat with other half of fruit, top with other crust and brown as before.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix and freeze at least half of it.
Take out of freezer about 6 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale.
Serves about 25 people.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Mix the mixed vegetables, tomato sauce and beef stew seasoning in a pot and let simmer on low heat until ground beef with chopped onions are brown.
Drain grease from ground beef and add ground beef and onions to the pot of mixed vegetables, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Add salt and black pepper.
Let simmer on low heat for about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas caviar
directions: In a bowl, combine the first nine ingredients; cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ham steak with raisin sauce
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and cornstarch.
Slowly add vinegar.
Add lemon juice, water and raisins.
Stir over low heat until thick. Heat ham thoroughly; place on a platter, stacked with 1/2 of sauce poured on each slice.

title: flavory fritters
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs with milk, flour, baking powder, salt and 1 tablespoon oil.
When smooth, fold in corn.
Pour enough oil into a large skillet to make it 1 inch deep and heat to 360°. Drop in corn mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until brown on one side, then turn and cook on the other side for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: apple sausage stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage; drain.
Add butter, onion and celery; saute 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in pie filling, broth and parsley.

title: mom's best chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass baking pan; add onions.
Pour soup over both and top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Make well in center. Add remainder of ingredients and mix well. Prepare 2 loaf pans. Grease and flour the pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes. Let loaves cool in pans for 2 minutes and remove from pans.

title: double rich chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside. In a large bowl, blend sugars with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add butter and beat to make a grainy paste.
Scrape down sides of bowl, then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips and blend at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 21 to 23 minutes.
Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool surface.

title: ranch dressing mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together until powdery in food processor or blender.
Makes 42 tablespoons of dressing mix.

title: quick black forest cake
directions: Beat eggs with almond extract.
Add pie filling and cake mix. Mix until blended, batter will be lumpy.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until it tests done in the center.
While cake is cooling, boil together sugar, milk and butter.
Add chocolate chips and stir until blended. Spread on warm cake.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Slice onion in bottom of casserole dish, then a thin layer of sliced potatoes.
Season layers as you go.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 pounds of hamburger on top of this, then tomatoes, rice and kidney beans. Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Cover with aluminum foil when you bake.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix pears, sugar and coconut. Let stand for 1 hour, stirring often. Sift flour, spices, soda and salt 3 times and add to pear mixture. Mix eggs, oil and vanilla. Add to pear mixture. Mix by hand. Pour into a well-greased tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and wash shrimp.
Combine all ingredients with mixer. This dip is good with raw veggies or with crackers.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute in butter, onions and celery.
Add salt and pepper, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix rice and broccoli all together.
Pour in shallow buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion and garlic in olive oil until tender but not brown. Stir in cumin, oregano, cayenne and cloves. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in beans, chili peppers and stock. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Stir in chicken and heat through. Ladle chili into bowls. Top each with 1/4 cup cheese. Dollop with sour cream and sprinkle chilies or jalapenos.

title: mama's favorite strawberry cake
directions: Mix together
and
flour
and grease 3 round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes and cool.

title: hershey torte
directions: Melt marshmallows, milk and chocolate in a double boiler.
Let cool to room temperature.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold the cream into the chocolate mixture.
Pour the mixture into the graham cracker crust and refrigerate overnight.
This makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, carrots and onion; drain and add celery soup and tuna.
Put in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: anise biscuits(delightful with tea)
directions: If using a nonpastry flour, add 1/2 teaspoon of baking powder.

title: broiled tomatoes with sour cream topping
directions: Peel tomatoes and slice in thick slices; drain well.
Place slices in flat dish and set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients and mix to make topping.
Spoon topping over tomatoes.
Place under preheated broiler and broil 3 to 5 minutes, or until thoroughly heated and bubbly.
Top with garnish and serve hot.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Mix dressing, preserves, onion soup and half of the dressing bottle of water all together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quiche
directions: Place slices of swiss cheese on bottom of crust. Sprinkle spinach, ham and mushrooms into crust. Mix eggs, 1/2 and 1/2 and salt. Pour into crust. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350 for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dairyland casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Brown beef; drain.
Add tomato and Worcestershire sauces.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream with softened cream cheese.
Add onions and green pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Cook in 325° oven until bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low calorie strawberry yogurt layer cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into two 9-inch round pans coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool pan on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Split each layer horizontally into 2 equal layers.
Place one layer on plate and top with yogurt.
Repeat procedure with 2 layers with the remaining layer covered.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Spread topping with whipped topping.
Freeze.
Garnish with fresh strawberries when serving.

title: janet's chili
directions: Brown ground beef with the onion, pepper and celery.
Add the rest of the ingredients and let simmer.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef until almost done, add the refried beans to the meat along with the cumin, garlic powder and oregano.
Set aside.
Mix the picante sauce and water together.
Put just enough to cover the bottom of a 9x13 pan (maybe 1/2 c.).
This helps to keep your noodles from sticking.
Place a layer of uncooked lasagna noodles on bottom.
Spread 1/4 of bean mixture over noodles.
Place second layer of uncooked noodles over bean mixture.
Top with another layer of uncooked noodles.
Pour remaining mixture of picante and water over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix the black olives, sour cream and green onions.
After removing lasagna from oven spread sour cream mixture over top, then sprinkle with Monterey Jack, pop back into the oven to melt cheese.
After removing from oven let it set for a few minutes.
Yield 8 servings.

title: key lime chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water and put aside.
On a low burner mix together 2/3 cup sugar, the egg yolks, lime juice and salt. Continuously stir this mixture and cook until it thickens somewhat. Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin.
Tint green as desired. Chill this mixture until it slightly thickens.

title: shannon's easy chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, combine 1 egg, 2/3 cup sugar, 1/2 cup milk and chocolate.	Cook and stir over medium heat until chocolate melts and mixture
comes	just to boiling.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening until
light.
Add vanilla and 2 eggs, one at a time, beating well
after each.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to
creamed
mixture
alternately
with 1 cup milk, beating after
each
addition.
Blend
in
chocolate
mixture. Bake in 2 greased
and
floured
x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Shannon's Fast and Easy Fudge Frosting.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Up to 1 hour before serving, combine coleslaw mix, green onions, Ramen noodles (save seasoning mix packet for the dressing), almonds and sunflower kernels in a salad bowl.
Cover and chill.
In a screw-top jar, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, pepper and seasoning mix from the package of noodles.
Cover and shake.
Chill.
At serving time, shake dressing again and pour over salad; toss to coat.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apricot nibble bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour.
Beat in 1 egg and orange peel.
Set aside.
Combine slightly beaten egg, orange juice, water and quick bread mix, stirring until moistened.
Turn 2/3 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Pour cheese mixture in and spoon on remaining batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool bread and remove from pan.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Discard drippings. Add onion, garlic, onion powder, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer uncovered about 10 minutes until most of liquid is evaporated. Pour 1/2 cup enchilada sauce into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange 6 shells on bottom of pan.
Spread another 1/2 cup of sauce evenly over shells.
Spoon in beef mixture.
Top with sour cream and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Put on remaining 6 shells and sauce. Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: polish sausage and cabbage
directions: Slice
onions
and
arrange
on
bottom
of Dutch oven. Slice potatoes and layer on onions and cover with water.	Salt and pepper
to	taste.	Cover
and
place on coals until water begins to simmer.	Cut cabbage into wedges.
When the water is simmering add the cabbage wedges and sausage and return to the heat.	Simmer until the potatoes are tender and the cabbage is wilted.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes.
Melt and mix all together. Serve hot with corn chips.
Will simmer great in a crock-pot.

title: "easy" oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt oleo, water and syrup in saucepan.
Mix in 1 cup of sugar.
Mix all dry ingredients together carefully.
Mix all together.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into small 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and shrimp gumbo
directions: First you boil the chicken with the first 5 spices and salt and pepper; boil until tender.
Strain broth off of chicken and save. Debone chicken and set aside.
Then you make a roux (gravy) out of the oil and flour, brown together over low heat.
Add the large onion and green pepper.
Saute for 3 minutes, then add broth to make a good gravy, then add the chicken pieces and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the fresh shelled shrimp.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
If you need more broth or water, add to this to make it a little soupier. Dip it over cooked shell-roni or noodles.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Crush tomatoes with hands so it will not be lumpy.
Add brown sugar
and	salt.
Mix
with
bread and put in buttered baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: date cake
directions: Pour hot water over the dates and cool.
Mix all the dry ingredients together with melted butter or margarine and eggs, then add dates and nuts.
Bake in layers or in a loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook hamburger, drain.
Add all ingredients but sour cream. Put on low heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add another 3 tablespoons garlic after heating.
Cook noodles; drain.
Pour stroganoff over noodles and serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave all ingredients together until melted.
Stir and pour into buttered rectangle dish.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: peach surprise cake
directions: Thicken peach liquid with 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Pour peaches and liquid in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry
cake mix over peaches.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Let butter soak into cake mix for at least 15 to 20 minutes; the longer, the better.
Sprinkle coconut, then pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned all over.

title: fried won ton
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and cornstarch well.
Put one tablespoon of beef and onion in center of square and fold it into a triangle.
Stick outer edge of wrapper with a little water and seal the won ton.
Heat 7 to 10 tablespoons of Crisco oil; fry won ton 6 at a time.
Use medium heat; fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Slice and layer bananas over bottom of pie shell.
Mix Jell-O pudding according to directions on box using skim milk.
Pour pudding over bananas.
Top with chocolate Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, cocoa, salt, sugar and baking powder. Add milk, vanilla, butter or oleo and nuts.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Mix and pour over batter, brown sugar, cocoa, white sugar and hot water.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mussel stew
directions: Scrub the mussels under running water with a hard-bristled brush, making sure to discard any mussel with an open shell.
Rinse in several waters to remove all the sand.
This is most important, as you will otherwise end up with a gritty stew.
Melt the chopped onion in the butter.
Add the mussels and all the other ingredients except the parsley and the extra butter.
No salt, please, for the mussels themselves are quite salty.
Put the saucepan on a fierce heat and cover with a glass plate so that you can see when the mussels open.
It takes only about 5 minutes.
When they are open, they are cooked.
Fish them out of the liquid and discard the empty top shell and the beard, keeping the shell to which the mussel is attached for serving.

title: salmon loaf ii
directions: Drain, debone and flake salmon.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, until top is golden brown and the loaf is firm, yet moist and tender.

title: aunt bill's brown candy
directions: Note:
It is easier if 2 people make this.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix oil, eggs, milk, pumpkin, cranberries and chopped nuts in another bowl.
Mix the 2 bowls together.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans or 8 miniature pans and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and unmold.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Pour broth into beaten eggs; add crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased dish.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: ham-broccoli bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
